title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip, milk and lemonade with mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Put in freezer for 1/2 hour.
Store in freezer or refrigerator.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs and margarine. Pour into a casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs and drizzle melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: husband's favorite beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, pour off excess fat.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, garlic, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Cover, simmer about 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Chop part of tops and bottoms on onions, finely.
Mix with cream cheese and sour cream.
Grease baking dish.
Put layers of noodles, meat, sour cream mixture and grated cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350° to heat thoroughly.
Best when mixed the day before. Serves eight with seconds.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Cut breast quarters across the breast into strips about 1/4-inch thick.
Place in a bowl with the teriyaki sauce and refrigerate overnight.
Cut up all vegetables.
Grate up carrot, chop bell pepper, onion, celery and sliced mushrooms.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together; pour over the peas and mushrooms and let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Heat milk to boiling point.
Beat in eggs and mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Brush pie crust with egg whites.
Pour custard into pie shell.
Bake approximately 15 minutes at 350°. Test by inserting a knife into the custard.
If the knife comes out clean, the pie is done.

title: honey beets
directions: Combine cornstarch, salt and water in a saucepan, stirring until blended.
Add vinegar, honey and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beets and cook until heated through, stirring constantly.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine mustard and honey.
Let stand a half hour so flavors can blend.
Makes about 4 dipping servings.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring continually until mixture thickens.
Add cheese and seasonings. Stir until cheese is melted.
Remove from fire and slowly add egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in a baking dish. Place dish in pan of hot water and bake 1 hour in a moderate 350° oven.
When brown and firm, remove from oven and serve.

title: pretzel salad(like cherry cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and pat down.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar. Stir in Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in frozen fruit.
Cool until partially set, then spoon over the cheese mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: never fail peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo, water, salt and peanuts in saucepan. Cook until temperature of 290° on a candy thermometer (hard crack).
Remove from heat and quickly stir in soda, vanilla and oleo.
Beat vigorously and spread on two greased cookie sheets. When cool enough to handle, stretch out to make as thin as possible; then break into pieces.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Sift dry ingredients flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix well. Add shortening, yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: custard pie (2)
directions: Method 1:
Preheat oven to 425°.
Line pie plate with pie crust.
Pur in custard mixture made by lightly beating eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Bake about 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce oven to 350° and bake until custard is firm.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add egg and mix with fork until beaded.
In baking dish, pour pie filling and top with dry mixture.
Melt oleo and dribble over top.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Add onion.
Cover with cooked rice.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes or until chops are tender.
Serves 4.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste with Chronicles 9:9.

title: new orleans skillet pork chops
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter and oil in heavy, deep skillet for 2 minutes, or until slightly softened.
Season pork chops with salt and pepper; brown on both sides.
Remove from pan; set aside.
Add water, brown sugar and 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce to skillet.
Bring to boil; stir in rice and fennel seed.
Return chops to skillet.
Spoon sauce and rice over them.
Cover; cook over medium low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour in remaining tomato sauce.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes, or until tender.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Fill crust with shrimp.
Top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour over shrimp and cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 40 or 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake at 325°.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press into 9 x 13 cake pan Pillsbury crescent roll dough.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dill weed.	Spread over cooled crust.
Chop finely any mixture of raw veggies that you want and spread over cheese topping.

title: homemade gravy
directions: After cooking your meat, pour off grease until just bottom of pan is covered.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in 2 to 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until nice brown roux (just before scorching).
Have hot water in bowl ready. Pour about half of water into roux.
Mixture will be thin.
Cook over medium heat, constantly stirring, until desired consistency is reached.
Tastes great with homemade biscuits and scrambled eggs.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into crust and freeze.
(There will be some leftover.)

title: fried bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Let cool until warm.
Add yeast; stir slightly.
Add flour and mix.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Roll out and cut into strips 1-inch wide, 3 inches long and 1/2-inch thick.
Deep fry in favorite shortening (no oil). Remove from fryer when browned; salt to taste.
Will puff in the center.
Serve with cheese, cold cuts, sausages and/or salads. Great for holiday parties.

title: potato medley
directions: Place oil, vinegar, orange rind, Dijon mustard, mustard seed, salt and pepper in food processor; process until well blended. Set aside.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Combine thawed and risen loaves and roll out on floured surface in 15 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spread generously with butter. Sprinkle with white sugar and cinnamon.
Roll from longest side; pinch ends together.
Cut in 12 slices.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Wash and cut cucumbers into sticks.
Pour boiling water to cover.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, pack pickle sticks into jars.
Cover with vinegar solution.
Seal jars; process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: islands peas and rice
directions: Dice bacon or ham into small pieces.
Fry crisp. Cut onion into small pieces.
Fry until golden brown.
Add tomato paste.
Fry a few minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: mississippi mud bar
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 jar marshmallow cream on top of cake just out of oven.

title: grilled chicken shish-ka-bob
directions: Marinate chicken, cut into 1-inch cubes, in onion soup mix, oil and water (overnight).
Load wooden or metal skewers alternately with meat and veggies until full.
Season with pepper. Grill for 10 to 15 minutes (ensure chicken is fully cooked between veggies).

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil 3 cans of sweetened condensed milk for 2 1/2 hours. Water must always stay above the top of cans so you will need to add hot water as needed. Then remove cans from water; let cool, then open and pour 1 1/2 cans in each already baked pie crust. Top with Cool Whip.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs; cream well.
Add cocoa with food coloring.
Add to cream mixture; add flour with milk.
Lastly, mix soda and vinegar; fold in cake mix.
Pour in 3 well-greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Cook cake mix by package directions.
Slice crosswise into two layers.
Mix pudding and milk.
Stir Cool Whip into pudding. Spread on cake.
Melt 1 can chocolate icing.
Spread or pour on cake.
(More attractive if poured on rather than spread.)

title: onion-garlic bread(home baked)
directions: Divide dough into 24 pieces. In a small bowl, combine onions, butter, cloves, parsley flakes and salt. Dip each piece of dough in this mixture. Place in a 10-inch tube pan that is sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about an hour. Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown. Serve warm with dabs of butter.

title: easy turtles
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line a baking sheet with foil.
Grease foil well.
Arrange pecans in clusters of 4, flat sides down, 1/2-inch apart.
Place 1 caramel on top of each cluster, pressing into pecans to flatten slightly and hold pecans together.
Place in oven; bake for 5 to 7 minutes, until caramels are soft.
Remove from oven; carefully flatten each caramel with a flat, buttered knife.
In a 1-cup glass measure, combine chocolate chips and oil. Heat in microwave on High 45 to 60 seconds, until smooth.
Spoon chocolate over Turtles, until covered.
Refrigerate 1 hour, until set.
Store and serve at room temperature.
Yields 2 dozen Turtles.

title: ample calhoun's old-time stackcake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add buttermilk and molasses; mix well.
Sift together all dry ingredients; add to other mixture and mix well.
Grease and flour 9-inch round pans. Spread thin in pans.
Make sure not to put too much batter in pans. Layers are thin.
Should make 8 to 10 layers.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
When layers are cool, stack with apple butter or cooked apples.
If cooking apples, add sugar and allspice to your taste.
Keep covered and in refrigerator.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Beat butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolk, egg and lemon juice.
Roll into balls.
Brush with egg white.
Roll in nuts that have been finely chopped.
Press thumb in center.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cold spread with jelly.

title: broccoli bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake for 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brandied fruit balls
directions: In a large bowl stir together all ingredients except confectioners sugar or coconut until well blended.
Using about 1 teaspoon of mixture, roll in balls; coat with confectioners sugar or coconut.
Place on wax paper-lined baking sheets; refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Store in refrigerator.

title: steak "a" round
directions: Marinate steak in refrigerator with first 8 ingredients for up to 3 hours.
Drain. In large skillet melt 2 tablespoons butter, add cubed steak and fry until brown, stirring often.
Remove from pan.
In same pan, add 3 tablespoons butter, celery, cabbage and onion.
Stir and cook until crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Heat through and then add beef and bouillon.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place partially thawed potatoes in crock-pot.
Stir in soup and milk.
Place 1/2 of onions in mixture.
Save rest to top dish with.
Cook on low for 8 to 9 hours.
Cook on high for 4 hours. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° until done.
Frost with Caramel Icing.

title: deer salami
directions: Mix spices with 1 cup water.
Add ground meat.
Mix well. Make into 3 to 4 rolls.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Seal ends.
Let set 3 days in refrigerator.
Put in cold water.
Bring to boil for 1 hour.
Take out of water.
Open foil.
Drain well, then wrap in foil and place in fridge.
Slice when cool.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a bowl and set aside.
Slice cucumbers and onions. Layer them in a gallon jar. Pour mixture over cucumbers and onions; put the jar in the refrigerator.
Shake the jar several times a day for 6 days, then they are ready to eat. Store pickles in the refrigerator.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: In
1-quart
saucepan, combine milk with rice, cinnamon and salt.
Bring
to a simmer over low heat and cook, covered, 30 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
In small bowl,
beat
egg
until
foamy,
then
beat in sugar and vanilla. Beat
a
little of the boiling rice mixture into egg mixture, pour back into saucepan with remaining rice mixture, stirring constantly.
Do
not
cook pudding after adding egg. Stir in raisins,
cool
10 minutes; pour into serving dishes. Chill several
hours or overnight, covered with plastic wrap. Serves 3.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: low cholesterol ranch quiche lorraine
directions: Marinate this with
1 cup no fat mayonnaise, 2 packets Sweet 'N Low and 2 tablespoons vinegar.

title: black forest roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan; then line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Grease the wax paper and dust lightly with flour, tap out excess flour and set pan aside.

title: fruit nog
directions: Blend at high speed until frothy. Add ice cubes, one at a time through opening in the lid. Blend until smooth; pour into frosted glasses and garnish with fruit of choice.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put into casserole dish. Cover top with slivered almonds and buttered bread crumbs (saute in butter, use generously).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Watch, don't burn top.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix together tomatoes, bell pepper, onions, pickles and cornbread.
In mixing bowl, combine pickle juice, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over salad and stir.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: coconut treasures
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Add butter, eggs, 2 tablespoons milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes vigorously by hand or at low speed of mixer.
Add remaining milk and coconut; beat 30 seconds longer.
Chill 2 hours.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from sheets at once.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: split pea soup
directions: Put water, ham bone, ham, peas and onions in a large stock pot.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix well and bake in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean).

title: beef with broccoli on noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain well. Marinate meat, ginger and soy sauce 30 minutes.
Heat oil in wok or pan.
Add meat, stirring constantly, until meat changes color. Mix other dry ingredients and add to beef stock and pour over meat in pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Add the onions and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Cook until hot.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and set aside.
Combine sugar, vinegar and salad oil. Mix vegetables and pour liquid over them.
Let set overnight.

title: quick chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Cut one onion and stalk of celery into pan.
Pour soup over all.
Cover with aluminum foil or use a dish with a top.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Chicken should be tender at pull.

title: shrimp and scallops linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions. Heat medium pan to medium high heat. Add olive oil, shrimp and scallops. Cook to 3/4 doneness; add garlic and sprinkle with pepper. Add wine. Cook for 15-30 seconds. Add cream and cook until desired thickness. Toss cooked linguine into shrimp and scallop mixture. Put pasta on plates and sprinkle with cheese. Garnish with parsley. Makes 2-3 entrees.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Alternate layers, ending with cheese on top. Heat in pot for 4 to 5 hours on low heat.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Peel when cool and dice.
Add ingredients and mix lightly.
Carefully fold in chopped eggs. Cover and chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a serving bowl and stir with a fork to blend thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Good served with raw veggies or chips.

title: mushroom omelet
directions: Combine mushrooms, onion, green pepper and garlic in 2 teaspoons margarine in small saucepan and cook until tender.
In another saucepan, blend water, soup, bay leaf, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper to taste and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Keep sauce hot.

title: caramel delights(turtles)
directions: Melt the caramels in top of double boiler (at least 20 minutes).
Add cream, stirring until smooth.
Add pecan halves. Drop by teaspoons onto a greased baking sheet.
Let stand until firm and not sticky to touch.
(They will set more quickly in the refrigerator.)

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Serve with Melba, Wheat Thins or gingersnaps.

title: double cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 3/4 cups water (boiling) in large glass bowl.
Use 2 to 2.5-quart size.
Let "set" in refrigerator until it starts to thicken, then stir in rest of ingredients.
Return to refrigerator until completely set.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put zucchini in pan uncooked. Brown meat and onion; add rice and seasonings.
Cover zucchini with meat mixture.
Spoon cottage cheese on top of meat.
Spread soup over cheese.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 50 minutes or until cheese gets a little browned.
This is very good.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in medium size pieces.
Cook in small amount of salted boiling water until half tender.
Remove from water and drain.
Mash, then add to taste minced onion, garlic, Romano cheese and small amount of olive oil; mix well.
Let cool. Add one beaten egg (or two if mixture is a large amount).
Add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle additional bread crumbs on top.
Bake in greased baking dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken sandwiches
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Then add to the stuffing the remaining ingredients.
Mix well; heat and serve.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and cook until brown.
Drain grease, then mix sausage with all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into large long Pyrex baking dish and bake in 350° oven until rice is tender.
Recipe can be divided.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix and then add milk.
Stir out lumps.
Cook over low heat.
I microwave until thicken.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let thicken.
Add to cool pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: one-step pork chop dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly oil a shallow baking sheet. (The pan should be wide enough to hold all the food in a single layer, with a little space between the ingredients.)
Wash and, if desired, peel carrots.
Cut them into 2-inch chunks.
Wash potatoes, peel (if desired)* and cut into 3-inch chunks.
Place carrots and potatoes in baking pan and sprinkle with a little oil. Toss to lightly coat the vegetables.
Make room for the pork chops and add to the pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and about 1 teaspoon of thyme, if using.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and oleo well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: shortcake
directions: Beat egg; add sugar and cream.
Sift flour and baking powder. Add 1 cup of flour to egg and sugar and mix.
Add milk; mix, then add remaining flour.
Add vanilla. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

Grease baking sheet with shortening. Combine shortening, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake 1 baking sheet at a time at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sausage-bean-escarole soup
directions: Crumble sausage without casing into deep, 3-quart microwaveproof casserole.
Add onion and garlic; microwave, covered, on High until sausage is cooked through, about 7 minutes. Trim escarole and tear white and light green leaves into bite size pieces.
Measure 3 cups packed leaves.
Break up sausage with fork.
Stir in escarole, cannellini beans with liquid, chicken broth, tomatoes with liquid, salt to taste, fennel seed and pepper.
Break up tomatoes with spoon.
Microwave, covered, on High for 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Place marshmallows and milk in double boiler and melt, set aside and cool, can put in pan of cold water to cool. When cool add: pineapple and cool whip. Can add crushed graham crackers for garnish.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Drain the oysters; measure 1 cup oyster liquor and reserve. Combine the crackers, butter, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle a third of the crumb mixture in the bottom of the baking dish.
Arrange half oysters over the crumbs.
Sprinkle another third of the crumb mixture over the remaining oysters. Whisk the cream, reserved oyster juice, the sherry (optional) and Worcestershire sauce together; pour over the oysters.
Sprinkle with the remaining crumb mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes; serve immediately.
(Leftovers will be good heated in microwave.)

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350°
for 15 to 17 minutes.
Let it sit a few minutes after removing from oven.

title: cream of garlic soup
directions: In large stock pot saute garlic in butter for 5 minutes at medium-high.
Stir occasionally so as not to brown the garlic.
Add pepper, bay leaves, wine and chicken stock.
Cook for 1 hour to reduce.
Don't cover.
If reduction is too severe, add 1 to 2 cups water.
After 1 hour remove from heat for 20 minutes to cool.
Add cream or half and half to pot, stirring constantly and return to medium-high temperature.
When the soup begins to steam, add roux to desired consistency.
If you have a wire whip this works best to stir.
Cook for 20 minutes more and serve.
Enjoy!

title: party punch
directions: Combine sugar and water and bring to a boil until sugar dissolves.
Add other ingredients.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on large cookie sheet and bake at 325 degrees for 15 minutes. Cool. Blend together miracle whip, cheese and dressing mix. Spread on cooled crust. Cover with vegetables of choice.

title: cherry punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in water with ice in a non-metal container. Add apple juice.
Makes 16 servings.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in margarine until tender. Combine broccoli, soup and cheese; cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Add sauteed vegetables to broccoli mixture.
Stir well and serve hot with Doritos or Fritos.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix well.
Pinch off pieces of dough about the size of a walnut and roll on floured board until thin.
Put a tablespoon of any kind of fruit in the center.
Wet edges to stick and fry. Pies can be frozen for later use.
Makes about 40 pies.

title: tortillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add shortening and blend well.
Add from 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 cups warm water, a portion at a time.
Knead well, shape into small balls, flatten and roll out with a rolling pin.
Place in a skillet that has been preheated to medium hot. Keep covered.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: crab canapes (or shrimp)
directions: Mix all ingredients except muffins.
Spread crab mix on cut muffins.
Freeze.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Spread 2 cups raw whole berries over bottom of baked shell. Mash or break remaining 2 cups berries, then add sugar, cornstarch and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Put over heat and bring to a boil.
Turn heat low and cook, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes. Cool.
Pour over raw strawberries in pie shell. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Top with whipped cream. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush cookies.
Melt butter and mix with cookie crumbs.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan to cover bottom.
Soften ice cream and spread over crust.
Freeze.
Cover with fudge topping, then Cool Whip. Freeze.

title: waffle and pancake syrup
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add flavorings.
Serve warm with pancakes and waffles.

title: chicken breasts with wild rice
directions: Cook wild rice following basic method on package.
Brown chicken breasts in butter and remove and set aside.
Brown onion, remove and set aside.
Brown almonds and mix rice, onion, almonds, mushrooms and pimento.
Place in buttered flat baking dish. Place chicken on top. Mix soup, sour cream, broth and salt and pepper.
Heat until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: low-fat shrimp, crab and rice casserole
directions: In a large heavy pot, pour stewed tomatoes.
Add garlic, green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender, approximately 20 minutes over low heat.
Add cream of mushroom soup, green onions, and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Contains 259 calories and 5.1 g. fat.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemonade,
Cool
Whip
and milk together.
Place in pie crust and put in refrigerator until firm.

title: overnight salad
directions: Place the ingredients in layers in the order given.
Mix the mayonnaise with a little milk or sour cream before adding.
Top the Parmesan cheese with a handful of frozen peas.
Do not stir. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift into bowl flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and cocoa. Stir in milk and butter.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square baking dish.
Mix brown sugar with cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Pour cold water over all.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold with cream or ice cream.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, egg, 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Stir in the chocolate chips and let stand.
Sift together the flour, 1 cup of sugar, cocoa, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add the water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well together until blended.
Fill cupcake papers 1/3 full with the chocolate batter, then top with heaping teaspoonfuls of the cheese batter and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: cock-a-leekie soup
directions: In a large pan, combine first 9 ingredients. Heat to a boil. Simmer 30 minutes. Add leeks. Heat to a boil. Simmer until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and let cool. When it is cool enough to handle, cut into bite-size pieces. Skim any fat from broth and remove bay leaves. Put chicken pieces back and reheat.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and roll into small balls about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Chill.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over warm water.
Use dipping fork to coat the chilled coconut centers.
Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine cheese and onion with enough mayo to hold mixture together (probably a slight 1/4 cup per can of peas).
Too much makes it soupy.
Mix well.
Gently fold in drained peas.
Let mixture set overnight or at least several hours for the flavors to combine.
(I usually double recipe for company and triple for picnics.)

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well and cut into slices.
Combine oil, cheese, salt, garlic powder, paprika and pepper in plastic bag. Add potatoes, a few at a time, and shake to coat.
Spread on cookie sheet in single layer.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars until light and fluffy. Add egg. Beat well. Add vanilla. Stir in. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well. Stir oats into mixture and mix well. Add chocolate chips. Shape into small balls and place on a greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from cookie sheet. Cool on racks. Yield: about 2 dozen.

title: custard mac' and cheese
directions: Mix all together.
Top with Kellogg's corn flakes crumbs or crumbs of your choice.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes to 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: inside-out chocolate bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a Bundt pan; combine all ingredients and mix well by hand.
Pour into pan; bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat all ingredients. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans (8 or 9-inch). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool before icing. (Can use two layer pans or tube pan but have to bake longer.)

title: brown rice
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam cabbage. Cook rice.
Chop onion and brown in skillet. Add meat, rice and milk (enough to moisten meat) and egg.
Peel cabbage leaves and cut rind.
Place meat mixture in center of rind end of leaf. Start rolling leaf.
Fold in sides and continue to roll to end of leaf.
Mix soup as directed.
Place cabbage leaves in bottom of pot.
Add some soup mixture.
Place cabbage rolls in pot and cover with soup mixture. Cook on top of stove for approximately 2 hours or until done.

title: fruit gelatin salad
directions: Put gelatine in ice cold water for 2 minutes.
Put Jell-O in dish and add 2 cups boiling water.
Add another 2 cups boiling water and stir.
Cool and add 4 cups of drained fruit juice and water as desired.
When thickens, add fruit or place fruit in serving dish and add gelatine mixture.

title: holiday ham
directions: Wash and scrub ham with brush.
Soak in cool water overnight. Drain and dry.
Place ham in deep roasting pan with fat side up. Mix horseradish and brown sugar; add raisins.
Brush on ham, reserving 1/2 cup.
Pour orange juice in bottom of pan; cover and cook at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover and place pineapple ring with toothpicks.
Fill rings with cherries and cloves.
Brush top with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until pineapple shrink.
Serve with applesauce and hot mustard.

title: aunt hattie's potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes.
Cook until potatoes are soft, but not mushy.
Let cool.
Blend other ingredients together and then add to potatoes.
Stir or mix until all is evenly spread.
Chill before serving.
Great for barbecues, picnics or any time.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mr. northcott's rolls
directions: Mix buttermilk, sugar, soda and Crisco.
Add dissolved yeast. Stir well until dough is formed.
No need to let rise.
Bake in muffin pan with compartments about 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
May be stored in tightly covered plastic bowl and refrigerate.
Use as needed.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in LARGE bowl. Add eggs and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas. Pour batter into tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done. (Insert a toothpick and it should come out clean.) Cool in pan for 10 minutes and then place on serving plate.

title: doritos chip dip
directions: Mix in a crock-pot and cook until hot.
Stir regularly.

title: best ever chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate in the top of a double boiler over hot water. Combine butter and powdered sugar in mixing bowl.
Beat well until smooth and creamy.
Beat yolks, one at a time, stirring constantly.
Stir in chocolate, vanilla and nuts (if used).
Chill until mixture is fairly thick, but not yet set.
Drop mixture into small paper cups or spread on baking sheet lined with waxed paper. Refrigerate until set.
Cut chocolate on baking sheet into bite-size pieces.
Makes about 30 pieces.
Preparation time: 25 minutes.
Chilling time: 1 hour.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put zucchini, butter and seasoning in skillet.
Cover.
Cook slow 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook turning slices until barely tender, about 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss. Serves 4.

title: quail casserole
directions: Place parsley, bay leaf and onion in the casserole then add quail, soup, salt and pepper or paprika.
Cover the dish and put into oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
When tender, make sauce as follows:
Heat 1 tablespoon butter and add 1 tablespoon flour; when light brown add sauce from the birds; when boiling, remove from heat and add sherry, mushrooms and catsup.
Pour over all the birds, return to the fire and when hot, serve in the casserole.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add bell pepper, celery and onions and cook until onions are clear.
Add soup; stir in crawfish.
Add rice and mix well.
Put in baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 3 layers at 325° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: brenda's icing
directions: Combine butter, Crisco, sugar and flavoring in mixing bowl. In saucepan, take 3 tablespoons flour and milk and bring to paste. Cool.
Put paste into mixture in mixing bowl and beat with mixer until desired consistency.

title: nutty chicken cheese potluck casserole(good recipe for low-carb diet)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: apple crisp(serves 6)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place apple slices in the pan.
Mix other ingredients thoroughly and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with light cream or ice cream.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: candied pecans
directions: Mix egg white and nuts. Mix sugar and spices. Pour over nut mixture. Bake in 300° oven for 25 minutes.

title: moist devil's food cake
directions: You can sour milk by adding 1 1/2 teaspoons vinegar to regular milk.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add soda to sour milk.
Let stand. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add sour milk alternately with flour and salt.
Add eggs.
Add chocolate.
Add boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes a deep, rich cake.

title: low-fat banana muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add bran cereal. Stir in mashed banana. Now add skim milk and Smart Beat. Beat egg white until peaks form and fold into mixture.
Spread muffin tin lightly with Smart Beat spread.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°. Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add tomatoes, soup and cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° until hot.

title: cil's pecan pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Dump in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Place chips in a medium bowl.
Microwave for 2 minutes or until chips are melted.
Stir every minute.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Spread candy evenly.
Refrigerate until firm.
Break into pieces.

title: carol's peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan, can of fruit with juice on top of margarine.
Pie fillings are best for this recipe.
Mix egg with flour and sugar.
Crumble on top of fruit and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry bavarian cream
directions: Drain strawberries keeping syrup in a cup.
Pour water over gelatin in bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Add enough cold water to syrup to make one cup.
Stir into gelatin.
Chill until almost set.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Saute
chopped	onion and minced garlic in 1 tablespoon salad oil.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, oregano and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes, remove the bay leaf and set aside.
Beat eggs with salt and
pepper.
Dip the sliced eggplant in the egg and fry in
salad oil
until
brown,
draining
them on paper towels. Place layer of eggplants in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon
half
of sauce over eggplants.
Sprinkle crumbs on top, repeat layers and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: butter crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large bowl.
Add milk, sugar, salt and egg, stirring until well blended.
Add 1 cup flour and beat until smooth.
(Don't worry if it doesn't dissolve all together, it will be fine.)
Add melted margarine; blend and set aside. Take another bowl and add the 1 cup cold margarine and remaining 4 cups of flour.
Cut the margarine and flour with a pastry blender or table knife until in fine particles like pie crust.
Pour the yeast batter into the flour mixture; carefully mix and blend well. Cover with clear plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours or 4 days.
Remove the dough to floured board and knead several times to release any air bubbles, then divide the dough into 4 equal parts.
Shape the portion to be used into a ball and refrigerate the rest.
Roll out into a circle about 17-inches.
Using a table knife, cut into 8 equal parts and roll up into a croissant shape. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; cover with dish towels and keep out of drafts.
They will rise in 4 to 5 hours.
In warmer weather, they will rise faster.
Rolls may be lightly brushed with the egg wash as they begin to rise.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
The complete recipe makes about 32 rolls.

title: blueberry sally lunn
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
In large bowl of electric mixer, combine butter, granulated sugar and eggs; beat at high speed until fluffy.
At low speed, add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Turn into pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake about 35 minutes.
Serve warm. Serves 9.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and flavoring.
Add pumpkin and nuts. Bake 1 hour at 275°.

title: fresh greens
directions: Wash greens (turnip, mustard, collard or a combination). Remove tough stems.
Cut bacon, salt pork or ham hocks in small pieces; add water and boil slowly.
Add black pepper and salt to taste.
Cook greens until tender.
Serve with cornbread.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and shortening together in mixing bowl. Dissolve yeast in warm water and let sit about 5 minutes. Add 2 C flour to the water, sugar, shortening and salt mixture. Beat until very smooth. Add egg and dissolved yeast. Beat until well blended. Stir in remaining flour one cup at a time.

title: fresh cucumber salad
directions: While cukes are setting, mix together sugar and vinegar.
Stir salt into cukes and onions.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well.
Add vinegar mixture.
Mix well.
Let stand a few minutes.
Serve.
May freeze these.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together the oil, eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon until well blended.
Add the baking soda, flour, water and pumpkin in small amounts.
Mix all together, stirring well after each addition.
Divide batter equally into 3 (1 pound) greased coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in the cans.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: *Or you may use 3/4 cup yellow corn meal, 1 cup white flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 3 1/2 teaspoons baking powder.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa until well blended; add milk, butter, egg yolks and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue and brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Top each bowlful with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips and sour cream.
Serve with shredded cheese.

title: texas patience
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and milk in heavy boiler.
Cook over medium heat until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat with mixer until it loses its gloss.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: hot spiced fruit punch
directions: Pour juices into a large coffee percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket and let perk.
Remove basket assembly after perking cycle has completed.
(This can be cooked on the stove on low setting.
Let juice simmer 30 minutes.
Wrap spices in cheesecloth so you can remove easily.)

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
While noodles are cooking, heat butter over medium heat until butter is melted. Stir in cream, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese and salt.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Drain noodles; toss with cream mixture until evenly coated.
Serve warm with Parmesan cheese, grated on top with ground pepper.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put into funnel; pour into hot, deep oil. Remove and drain.
Sprinkle with xxxx sugar.

title: chess pies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients and put in shells.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dove delight(pet)
directions: Pour sand or grit into plastic container that is 2 to 3 inches deep.
To that, add any amount of listed ingredients.
Replace sand as often as necessary, especially after rain or snow.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, salt and onion in a bowl; soak for 2 hours. Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Put pickles in containers; put in freezer.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in lightly greased casserole dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.

Add Velveeta cheese and stir until cheese is melted. Put mixture on slices of party rye bread. Place under broiler of stove on a cookie sheet and heat until lightly browned on top. Serve hot. Note: These may be frozen and browned under the broiler whenever you need them.

title: princess gem cookies
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add ammonia crystals and sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add flour, a little at a time. Add coconut and form into small balls.
Place 1 inch apart on baking sheet and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar immediately after baked.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: To thin, use milk.
Pour 1/4 cup melted margarine or butter over finely chopped pecans on top.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat. Blend next 4 ingredients and stir in cheese.
Add onion and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Chop onions and peppers.
Brown meat with onions and peppers. Drain grease and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 80.

title: johnnycake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
Add corn meal and mix. Combine rest and add to mixture.
Stir only enough to dampen flour. Press into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Mix well together.
Let stand 1 hour. Cook 30 minutes, stirring often, until thick.
May use a few drops of oil of cinnamon instead of candy.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add and blend the baking soda, vanilla, corn syrup and peanut butter.
Blend in the oatmeal for 1 minute, then chocolate chips, M&M's and pecans. Drop dough by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (10 to 12 minutes).

title: tortilla black bean casserole
directions: In a large skillet, combine onion, green peppers, undrained tomatoes, picante sauce, garlic and cumin.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in beans.

title: snowballs
directions: In large bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, salt and butter; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour.
Work nuts into dough.
Chill well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set, but not brown.
Roll in sugar immediately.
Cool on rack.
Roll in sugar again.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: dressed-up dogs
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in milk just until moistened. Turn onto a floured surface; knead 10 to 12 times. Roll into a 12-inch circle. Brush with butter; sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Cut into 12 wedges. Place hot dogs at wide end of wedges and roll up. Place on an ungreased baking sheet with point down. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 12 servings.

title: cloverleaf potato rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine potatoes, butter, sugar, salt and milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and eggs.
Stir in 4 cups of flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover, let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Punch down.
Shape in ball.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes. (Dough may be refrigerated for 1 week if kept covered by damp towel.)
When ready to use, shape in cloverleaf rolls (three 1-inch balls pinched together at bottom); place in greased muffin pans. Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen rolls.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Combine ingredients. Fill 1/2 full in greased muffin tins (miniature tins). Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit soup
directions: Puree all fruits in a blender.
Add apple juice or artificial sweetener as desired.
Chill and garnish with sprig of mint leaves.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups of soup.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a simmer.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, oleo and milk.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water for 8 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine tuna and all other ingredients with macaroni.
Add mayonnaise and/or horseradish to tuna/macaroni mixture.
Toss gently.
Add more mayonnaise, if desired.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Garnish with green pepper strips and tomato slices.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put hamburger meat in bottom of baking dish.
Layer 2 cans cream of mushroom soup on top of meat.
Then, layer package of Tater Tots on top of soup layer.
Put in oven and bake until Tater Tots are browned.
Add Cheddar cheese and cook until cheese melts.

title: african chow mein
directions: Saute onions, beef and veal. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and bake in buttered casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: rotini feta salad
directions: Place water in a 3-quart microwavable casserole.
Cover with lid.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes or until water boils.
Stir in pasta and re-cover.
Stirring midway through cooking, microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until done.
Drain and cool slightly. Return pasta to same casserole and toss with dressing.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve.

title: diabetic banana bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin tins with Pam if needed. In medium size bowl, sift together flour, Sweet 'N Low and baking powder; stir in Bran Flakes.
In separate bowl, dissolve baking soda in milk.
Blend margarine, honey, molasses, banana and egg. Combine with milk.
Beat with fork or whisk to mix thoroughly. Make well in center of dry ingredients.
Pour in liquid ingredients; stir quickly until dry ingredients are just moistened and mixture is slightly lumpy.
Divide batter into muffin cups, filling each 2/3 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fat-free brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Brownies should not be overcooked until dry, but should "glisten" on top after baking.

title: wedding shrimp(4 servings)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake until shrimp are cooked through, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Garnish with lemon wedges and serve shrimp with French bread.
Great with rice, too.

title: rum sauce(cooked)
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Drizzle over rum cake, bread pudding, etc.

title: cheese squares
directions: Grate both cheeses and mix.
Beat eggs and add milk and flour.
Layer cheese, then chilies, then salt, then pepper, ending up with a layer of cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Freezes well, but add egg mixture last.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: mini apple pizzas
directions: Roll biscuits into 3 1/2-inch circles.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
In bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Add apples and mix.
Spoon rounded tablespoon onto biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until edges begin to brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan. In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together applesauce, oil sugars and eggs.
Blend in flour, beating until smooth.
Stir in carrots. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 60-65 minutes or until done. Remove cake from pan.
Cool completely.
Glaze cake if desired. Serves 24.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until dry.
Cool.
Add eggs, applesauce, sweetener and oil.
Add flour, cinnamon and soda mixed together. Pour into a 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350 degree until done. This cake is very tasty.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add nuts and raisins or dates and coat well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Blend well.
Turn into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake in a 325° oven for 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
Leave in pan for at least 1 hour.
Turn over and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar or confectioners sugar.

title: basic vegetable soups
directions: Cook until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: no bake peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Form into walnut-sized balls. Chill in refrigerator.

title: apricot punch
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Makes 50 servings.

title: grape-nuts custard
directions: Scald milk and Grape-Nuts in microwave approximately 13 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Mix with milk and Grape-Nuts in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon on top.
Cook on High, approximately 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together, then beat in eggs.
Add buttermilk and flavoring.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° until firm, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; stir in peanut butter. Add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls; mash with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: cranberry crunch cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until well combined.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and vanilla to egg mixture.
Fold in cranberries.
Spread batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with marshmallows.
Press into batter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: ernie's broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the cornbread mix.
Add mix last. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°. Serve hot.
Do not overbake.
Delicious with soup on cold days.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Combine pineapple and sugar.
Cook 3 minutes; add Jell-O.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Stir in cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: grandmother's boiled fruit cake
directions: Add the sugar, raisins and shortening to the water and boil 3 minutes.
Cool and add soda, spices and flour.
Mix to a smooth batter and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in hot oven for about 30 minutes.

title: spiced pot roast
directions: In large pot, brown meat with Gravy Master.
Stick the cloves in the meat.
Slice onions on top of the meat.
Add water, vinegar and bay leaves.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Add water as needed.
When nearly done, add carrots, whole string beans and potatoes.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add cocoa
and mix.
Add sugar and milk. Stir with wooden spoon.Stir occasionally until it comes to a rapid boil.

title: key lime crispies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add the eggs and oil and beat well. Combine flour, baking soda, and salt. Stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture along with the Key lime juice.

Beat until smooth and well mixed. Roll the dough into small balls about 1 inch in diameter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet, spacing cookies about 2 inches apart. Using the bottom of a glass dipped into sugar, flatten the balls. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.
Remove from the pan immediately to a wire rack. Dust with confectioners' sugar.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: leicester kid's place pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add vegetable oil, egg and milk.
Mix all together.
May add more milk to desired thickness. Makes 6 to 8 medium size pancakes.

title: best coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, in 2 round cake pans. Once cooled, split cake layers to make 4 layers. Mix remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Spread filling between layers, saving 1 cup of filling. Mix with Cool Whip and spread on top and sides of cake.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Use liquid from strawberries, pineapple and enough water to make 2 cups.
Make jello with this hot liquid.
Add fruits and pour 1/2 of mixture into an 8 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread sour cream on top and then pour other 1/2 of mixture on top of sour cream.
Refrigerate; eat.

title: best in ky baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and cut up sausage.
Drain fat.
Mix with all remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or in crock-pot on low overnight.

title: blueberry cheese dessert
directions: Mix vanilla wafer crumbs, nuts and melted butter.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients as listed in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake in greased and floured tube pan about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Recipe calls for 1 teaspoon cloves, but it's optional.

title: praline bars
directions: Arrange crackers in single layer in jelly roll pan.
Heat brown sugar and butter to boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute (no longer); remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over crackers; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into bars, about 2 1/4 x 1 1/4-inches, each cracker into two bars.
Use ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Yield:
48 bars.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onions.
Mix all ingredients together and heat.
Do not boil.

title: the best layered taco party dip
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning; set aside. IN a large 9 x 13-inch glass dish, layer the following in order: bean dip, avocado dip, taco seasoning mixture, onion, tomato, olives and sharp Cheddar cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and pat into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake 8 minutes at 375°.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: icebox no bake fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk together over warm low heat or double boiler.
Mix remaining ingredients into marshmallow and milk mixture.
Mix well and press in a greased bowl or tube pan.

title: hot cinnamon cranberry punch
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add sugar and red hots.
Stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add cloves and frozen juices. Stir; then cover and let stand until cool.
Add cranberry juice. Serve hot or cold.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: nut bread
directions: Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.

title: caramel chocolate cookie bars
directions: Melt evaporated milk and caramels.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup plus 1 tablespoon evaporated milk and melted margarine. Spread slightly more than 1/2 of mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread caramel mixture over this. Crumble rest of cake mixture on top.
Bake until sides pull away from pan, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix and form your meat balls.
Put in baking pan.

title: colonial chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
In a large frying pan brown chicken on all sides.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In second bowl mix 4 eggs and milk until light, then mix in butter.
Slowly blend
egg mixture into dry mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken in batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork normandy
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook pork chops about 10 minutes or until browned;
spoon
off fat.
Stir in soup, apple juice, apples, celery and thyme.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover;
simmer until
tender,
stirring
occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked egg noodles.
Garnish	with apple slices, if desired.	Serves 6.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine melted margarine, brown sugar and pretzels.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add broth and potatoes; simmer 10 minutes.
Add chopped, cooked shrimp, crab meat and eggs.
Add clams, cream and milk; heat, but do not boil.
Mix all. Blend flour to desired thickness.
Pour in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: large pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and oleo or margarine; add eggs, one at a time.
Then add flour a little at a time.
Also add part of the milk until you use all the flour and the milk, beating well with a mixer.
Add vanilla extract, if desired, and cream all well. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan and pour batter in pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Grease and
flour
a
13 x 9-inch pan.	Mix ingredients and blend
thoroughly.	Pour
into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Break bran flakes up with fingers.
Stir in sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Stir in eggs, milk, oil, juice and pieces of orange. Add raisins and dates.
Put in refrigerator for 1 day or longer. Fill paper cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 48.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice by package directions, cooking until not quite done, with a little water left.
Mix all ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Put in Ziploc bag. Wash chicken.
Dip in melted margarine. Shake in plastic bag.
Place in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spice and applesauce cake
directions: Pour oil into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put cake mix, eggs and pie filling into pan (you may add 1 cup of raisins and nuts).
Stir with a spoon until blended.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: tamale chicken
directions: Mix garlic powder, pepper and chili powder.
Rub into skinned chicken.
Fry lightly, cover with tomatoes and cook on low until tender.
Debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Save 1 cup tomato liquid and tomato chunks.
Fry onion and green pepper; add cut-up tamales, soup, sour cream, tomato sauce, tomatoes, olives (drained) and chicken pieces.
Pour into casserole, cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pudding pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients into a bowl.
Blend at low speed to moisten.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pan.

title: orange scallops
directions: Combine zest, juice, oil and scallops in plastic bag. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Melt bouillon cube in hot water; add potatoes, carrots, celery, onions, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
In a small pan, combine milk and flour, stirring until thickened.
Add to potato mixture; add cubed cheese and stir until cheese is melted.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix all together in a casserole.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and cook spinach; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze (couple of days).
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: wedding punch
directions: Soften all froze ingredients and place in punch bowl (no water).
Mash until mixed.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale. Mix very little.
Punch for 50 people.

title: ziti pasta with spicy marinara primavera sauce
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, add tomatoes and break them up into smaller pieces.
Add jar of salsa, garlic, onion and spices.
After about 10 minutes, turn down heat to low and add rest of ingredients (except for peppers and noodles).
Allow to simmer on very low heat (covered) for about one to two hours, stirring often, so that spices and flavors may blend.
Add peppers about 20 minutes before removing sauce from heat.
Cook noodles in boiling water and drain.
Combine noodles and sauce; serve. Serves six (or four, if they are really hungry!).

title: finger paint
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.	Stir in white glue and color of choice.	This works well on the slick side of freezer paper. Kids love this!

title: broccoli bread
directions: Drain broccoli.
Melt oleo in black skillet.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl and add oleo; pour into skillet and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
This is so good!

title: johnny mazette
directions: In a very large skillet, saute pepper, celery, onion and ground meat in very hot butter
Add salt.
Reduce heat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms, soup and sauces.
Cook 5 minutes. Cook noodles; drain.
Turn noodles into a 14 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch roasting pan.
Add sauce mixture and olives;
gently stir until well mixed.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: apricot-pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with one crust. Brush crust with butter.
Place a layer of apricot halves over butter.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, tapioca and salt.
Put half of sugar-flour mixture over apricots.
Put half of pineapple on sugar-flour mixture.
Repeat layers.
Pour butter on top. Cover with other crust.
Puncture several times to let steam out. Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: asparagus baked with parmesan cheese
directions: Wash asparagus; break off hard ends.
Steam asparagus in water for about 12 minutes; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Butter a glass baking dish and put a layer of asparagus in the bottom.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, grated cheese and crumbs of butter (it's easier to crumble if it's cold).
Add another layer of asparagus, then cheese, and so on, until you have used all the asparagus. The top layer should be cheese and butter.
Put into a medium oven (325°) until the cheese is golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Marinate chicken in lime juice and salsa mixed together 2 hours or overnight.
Saute chicken until cooked.
Put remaining marinade in pan and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Pour water over chocolate chips and let stand 1-2 minutes.	Stir.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs in a very large bowl. Put in a greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch will work) and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bring first 4 ingredients to boil in a saucepan.
Place flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Pour the boiled mixture over it and stir. Add last 4 remaining ingredients and mix in the large bowl with beater about 3 minutes.
Batter is thin.
Pour in cake pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables (i.e. carrot sticks, celery sticks, cauliflower, broccoli, etc.).

title: baked banana surprise(one for the kids)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place whole, ripe unpeeled banana on cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes. Split baked banana with knife. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve inside the banana peel.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Grind oranges and lemon in meat grinder, rind and all.
Put in layers the peaches, sugar, oranges and lemon and cook until it begins to thicken. Do not cook in large quantities, not more than 5 lots.

title: cheese veggie lasagna
directions: Heat oil in skillet and saute onion and garlic until lightly brown and tender.
Add spinach and carrots and desired amount of salt and pepper and continue cooking for several minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, mozzarella cheese and Swiss cheese together and mix well.
Add spinach mixture to the cheese and mix well.
Place 1/3 of this spinach-cheese mixture at the bottom of a 13 x 9 inch baking dish that has been sprayed with non-stick spray.
Place 4 or 5 noodles on top of the mixture, then 1/3 more of mixture and 4 or 5 more noodles.
Place the remaining mixture on top and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350 degrees. Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes before cutting and serving.
For meat lovers, just layer some cooked ground beef or sausage in between the mixture and noodles.

title: lo-cal key lime pie
directions: Blend these two and press into 8-inch pie pan.

title: frank's fantastic baked beans
directions: Melt butter until it comes to a sizzle; then drop in the onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute the mixture for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce, barbecue sauce and brown sugar; simmer over low heat for 15 minutes (uncovered).
While sauce is cooking, take a 9 x 11-inch baking dish and grease it lightly. Pour pork and beans into baking dish.
When sauce is smooth and shiny, pour over beans and mix it well.
Place the beans in a 375° oven and bake, uncovered, for about 35 to 45 minutes or until the top turns dark brown.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve with fresh strawberries, etc.

title: party punch
directions: Mix with mixer.
Make shortly before serving.

title: easy pecan cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in flour, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Turn onto cake plate.

title: salad
directions: In small saucepan combine orange flavored and unflavored gelatins, sugar and juice from pineapple.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, until gelatins and sugar are dissolved, stirring constantly.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add pineapple, orange juice, yogurt, carrots and salt.
Chill 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Coat an 8-cup mold with Pam.
Pour mixture into mold. Chill overnight until firm.

title: cotton pickin' cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil at medium speed. Pour evenly into 3 greased layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 22 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients, with exception of spaghetti.
Simmer until done, adding water as needed.
When thoroughly cooked, add precooked spaghetti and heat together.

title: light bread apple treat(microwave oven)
directions: Mix together apple, spice and sweetener in microwave-safe bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap; leave one edge open to vent steam.
Microwave (High) about 2 minutes, until apples are soft. Makes 1 to 2 servings.

title: quick surprise potato rolls
directions: Mix together lukewarm water, potatoes (packed in cup), sugar and salt.
Crumble yeast into mixture.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Add shortening.
Mix in flour with spoon or hand. Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes to tighten up.
Then knead until smooth and elastic. Round up and divide in 2 parts to make dough easy to handle.

title: old-fashioned chicken-n-dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and bake.
Let cool.
Boil 1 large fryer. Take meat off bone.
Chop real fine.
Add tablespoon of butter. Mix bread mixture and chicken well, adding broth from boiled chicken.
Put in large pan and bake until brown.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add the nuts, dates, coconut, eggs and vanilla.
Spread mixture about 1/2-inch thick in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove pan from oven. Cut and roll in balls and then in granulated sugar.

title: mock steak
directions: Pack in
pan or make in rolls.	Chill overnight.
Slice next morning
and
brown.
Cover with 2 cans cream of mushroom soup (in layers).
Some water may be added if desired.
Put in oven and bake 1 or 2 hours.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a very large mixing bowl.
This is very important.
Add beaten eggs, shortening and buttermilk; mix well.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator and use as desired.
Fill in greased tin 2/3 full and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep refrigerated for 6 weeks.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli stalks into about 1-inch pieces.
Cook in 1-inch of boiling water for about 10 to 15 minutes or until just done. Drain; chill broccoli.
In screw-top jar, combine vinegar, soy sauce, oil and sugar.
Cover and shake to mix well.
Drizzle vinegar mixture over broccoli; toss gently.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gooey coffee cake
directions: Mix softened butter and 3 ounces cream cheese with cake mix until well blended. Add 1 egg and blend well. Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: creamed cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in 1-inch of water with salt.
When boiling, reduce the heat, cover and simmer for 6 minutes.
Drain and put in casserole.
Sprinkle with 4 Tbsp. bread crumbs or crushed croutons. Pour half and half over vegetable. Dot with butter and sprinkle 2 tsp. crumbs over top.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Garnish with fresh parsley if desired.

title: chocolate malted cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; beat for 2 minutes. Add egg. Combine the flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition. Stir in chocolate chunks and chips. Shape into 2-inch balls. Place 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 2 minutes before removing to a wire rack. Yield: about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl. Beat 12 minutes. Pour into greased, floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except butter, crackers and almonds.
Place chicken mixture in casserole dish.
Mix together crackers, butter and almonds.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rye bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients and let bubble.
After yeast mixture bubbles, beat in 5 cups whole wheat flour.
Beat by hand or with an electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Let set about 5 to 10 minutes, then mix in rye flour, salt and caraway seed.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes, adding remaining half cup of whole wheat flour as needed.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down dough and form into 2 large loaves or 3 small loaves.
Place in "Pammed" loaf pans.
Let rise until bread is about 1 inch above the pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eat anytime soup
directions: Combine carrots, onion and bell pepper and cook in microwave for about 5 minutes or until tender.
Combine all ingredients in a large boiler and simmer until flavors blend and cabbage is to the texture you want.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Make jello according to directions on box.
Chill until partially set up.
Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces. Mix jello, Cool Whip and strawberries together and stir in angel food cake.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: fancy walnut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 24 foil cupcake liners on baking sheets.
Combine brownie mix, egg, 1/3 cup water and oil in large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended.
Stir in contents of walnut packet from mix.
Fill each cupcake liner with 2 generous tablespoons of batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until set.
Cool completely, then remove liners and turn brownies upside down on cooling rack.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Sauce:
Combine all ingredients; ready to use.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Leave cream cheese out to soften for 1 hour before starting. Mix Fluff and cheese until smooth with electric mixer.
Wash and pit strawberries; place on plate or dip dish.
Add Fluff mix to a bowl in center.
Quick and easy dip.
Other fruits can be used.

title: buried treasure
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed.
Using a spoon, scoop out 4 balls of frozen whipped topping and place in each of 4 dessert glasses.
Spoon pudding over whipped topping in glasses.
Chill. Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: splenda apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples and slice or chop.

Combine cinnamon and sugar; stir until mixed. Spray a 9 x 13 casserole dish with Pam. Place apples into casserole dish. Top with cinnamon and sugar mixture. Pour soda over apples; pour melted margarine over apples. Layer crescent rolls over apple mixture, laying wide ends to narrow ends to form good coverage. Sprinkle chopped pecans over rolls and bake at 375° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes. Serve with a scoop of ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: spinach balls
directions: Prepare spinach by package directions but under cook by a few minutes.
Drain well and squeeze to remove excess moisture. Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 3/4 inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 80 appetizers.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Drop into hot soup and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: lemon sauced sole
directions: Sprinkle fillets with pepper; dredge in flour.
Dip in egg whites; dredge in flour again.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add 1/2 teaspoon margarine and place over medium heat until hot.
Add 2 fillets; cook 4 minutes on each side or until fish is lightly browned and flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Set aside and keep warm.
Repeat procedure with remaining margarine and fillets.
Add wine and remaining ingredients to skillet.
Cook until mixture reduces to 1/4 cup.
Spoon over fish.

title: artichoke spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Stir Parmesan cheese into casserole and also sprinkle some on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans in colander; press down to squeeze out water.
Set aside.
Cube Velveeta and melt over low heat in nonstick pan or microwave.
Add drained green beans and 3/4 can of onions.
Continue heating until cheese is hot and melted.
Top with remaining onions and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: large sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Put into sifter and add cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Sift and set aside.

title: golden scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion, soup mixture and cheese.
Dot top with butter; sprinkle with paprika. Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more or until potatoes are done.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: orange julius
directions: Place ingredients into blender.
Mix until well blended and foamy. Add ice cubes, two at a time, while blending until desired consistency.
(Sugar can be reduced.)

title: mexican burrito pie
directions: Combine beans, biscuit mix and water in a medium bowl; mix well.
Spoon bean mixture into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate to form a pie shell.
Set pie shell aside.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Roll level tablespoonfuls of mixture into balls (makes about 60). Arrange them on cookie sheet (with sides is best), close but not touching.
At this point, they can either be frozen and put in a gallon Ziploc bag or cooked in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until firm.

title: salisbury steak deluxe
directions: Blend soup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine beef with 3/4 cup of this mixture.
Add egg, bread crumbs, onion and salt.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown in skillet.
Drain off fat. Stir in soup mixture, water and parsley.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes, stirring gently occasionally.

title: broccoli-ham strata
directions: Cut rounds of bread with cutter and set aside.
Place scraps of bread in bottom of 9x12 greased pan.
