Layer cheese, then broccoli, then ham over bread.
Arrange bread rounds on top of mixture.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Grate (extra) cheese for topping.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain any grease.
Add taco seasoning and mix. Then add sauces.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 meat mixture into casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 crushed Doritos and repeat process. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with shredded cheese.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Bring to boil sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa. Boil for 1 minute (no longer) and remove from heat. Add peanut butter and quick oats. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: old world tomato soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter.
Add tomatoes, broth, seasonings and cornstarch combined with water.
Simmer 15 minutes. Stir in cooked bacon.
Top with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: To bacon drippings, add flour, sugar and salt. Cook until bubbly.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.

title: squash relish
directions: Soak squash, onions
and
bell
pepper in salt water (3 quarts water and 2/3
cup canning salt) for 1 hour.
Pour off. Make up remaining
ingredients.
Bring
to boil.
Drop vegetables into brine.
Bring
to
boil
again, then put in jars and seal.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Mix the oil and thyme with the dressing mix in cup and pour over crackers, covering well. Shake with garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Bake at 200° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store in Ziploc bags or tins.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, water and shortening into a bowl until well blended.
Drop batter by 1/2 teaspoon into a bowl of confectioners sugar.
Coat well and roll into balls.
Put onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pickled red onions ala cia
directions: Blanch onions until limp; drain well.
Combine all other ingredients; pour over hot onions.
Marinate for 4 hours.
Chill or serve at room temperature.
Will keep up to 1 month, refrigerated.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: balsamic potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling salted water over medium heat until just tender.
Meanwhile make balsamic dressing. Whisk sour cream, vinegar, olive oil, salt and pepper in a large bowl until blended.
Stir in all but 2 tbsp. sliced scallions. Drain potatoes well in colander.
Transfer to bowl, add dressing and gently toss to coat.
Let potatoes cool to room temperature. Add celery and radishes to potatoes and toss gently to combine. Line serving bowl with romaine leaves and spoon potato salad onto lettuce.
Sprinkle salad with reserved scallions.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and place in 1 1/2-quart to 2-quart microwave dish.
Combine remainder of tomato sauce and other ingredients into a smooth sauce.
Pour over loaf.
Cook 20 minutes on High, uncovered, in the microwave.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and stir until thoroughly combined.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
(Cookies will not seem done at this point.)
Leave cookies on baking sheets for a few minutes until they become firm.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place corned beef in a large Dutch oven and put in enough water to just cover meat.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and add bay leaf.
Cook for 3 hours or until tender.
Add cabbage and potatoes.
Cook until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp, olives, tomatoes and cucumbers with dressing. Stuff into pitas with lettuce.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and sausage well by hand.
Add Bisquick; shape into walnut size balls.
Place in shallow pan or on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 dozen or more.
Can be served for breakfast, brunch or parties.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix egg yolks and lemon juice together.
Add cream cheese and condensed milk.
Mix on high speed.
Place layer of crackers on a plate or Pyrex dish.
Place a layer of filling and layer of crackers until all filling is used.
Do not cook.

title: veal with vegetables over pasta
directions: Brown veal cubes in olive oil and garlic.
Add white wine and simmer for about 5 minutes. Add vegetables and tomato sauce.
Let simmer until vegetables are firm, but tender.
Prepare pasta. Pour over pasta and serve with grated cheese.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased Pyrex dish (11 x 13-inch) at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Pour scalded milk over eggs and sugar. Add vanilla and mix well. Pour into custard cups or casserole dish.
Sprinkle liberally with nutmeg.
Set in pan of hot water and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: double delicious halloween bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine; pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: peanut butter snack(good for kids)
directions: Mix together peanut butter and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and form into little balls.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.

title: venison swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt, and pepper.
Dredge steak in flour mixture.
Heat oil in skillet and brown meat.
Place in slow cooker.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Cook on low 7 1/2-8 1/2 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Into a large bowl, mix all ingredients except raisins with mixer at low speed.
Beat until well mixed, constantly scraping the bowl.
Beat at high speed 3 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Dressing for above ingredients:
mix 1 c. mayonnaise & 1 c. sugar.
For larger batch use more dressing.
Mix together and serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a large 8-quart pan, put milk, rice and butter.
Cook 50 to 55 minutes on medium heat, so that it boils slowly.
Keep on stirring with a wire whisk.
Beat 6 eggs, sugar and vanilla with whisk.
Add to rice last 5 minutes and let them cook together. Put in a bowl or 9 x 12 x 3-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Always keep it with a slow boil.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients until soft dough is formed.
Roll and cut out small biscuits.
Place pecan half on each. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix all but Tater Tots in casserole dish. Top with Tater Tots. Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: brussels sprouts with mustard sauce
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, put Brussels sprouts and water; cover tightly and microwave on High for 8 to 11 minutes or until tender. Drain in colander and rinse under cold tap water. In saucepan, melt margarine over low heat; stir in mustard, beef broth, lemon juice and pepper. Blend until smooth (about 1 minute). Coat Brussels sprouts with sauce.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix and cook 20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal. If made in smaller quantities it can be kept in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Beat yolks and buttermilk together.
Add dry ingredients with melted butter.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake on hot griddle.
Good with a few blueberries added onto batter before turning over.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix milk, sugar and vanilla in boiler and boil for 3 minutes. Add crushed saltine crackers and peanut butter.
Stir rapidly and be sure that crackers and peanut butter are premeasured.
Candy gets hard very fast.
Pour in buttered dish.

title: orange-glazed ribs
directions: Place ribs, meaty side down, in shallow roasting pan.
Roast in 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; drain off excess fat.
Turn ribs, meaty side up.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°; continue roasting 30 minutes more.
Combine marmalade, soy sauce, lemon juice and ginger; spoon half of the sauce over the ribs. Roast 30 minutes more or until tender, spooning remaining sauce over occasionally.
Garnish ribs with orange slices, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan; bring to boil. Remove from stove and let cool for about 20 minutes.
Return to stove and bring to full rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: "dirt"
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside. Mix milk and pudding together until almost set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix in cream cheese mixture.
`Blend Oreos in food processor until powdery.
Place 1/2 in 8-inch flower pot.
Add pudding mixture, then remaining Oreos.
Place artificial flowers in top.

title: punch
directions: In a punch bowl, mix together orange and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale.
Sherbet may be added whole or you can divide into chunks.
Use as much as you desire.
Tastes better if allowed to set for a few minutes.
This allows sherbet to melt a little bit and blend in with the juices.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken into a baking dish that has been sprayed with Weight Watchers spray.
Slice veggies and mushrooms; lay on top and all around the chicken.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cream pudding and cream cheese together.
Add milk and mix until pudding becomes thick.
Stir in whipped cream.
Add bananas and vanilla wafers.
Makes a large pudding.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Soften cheese and butter at room temperature.
Cream with mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread on split muffins.
Cut each half into four wedges.
Spread on cookie sheets and cover with waxed paper.
Freeze if not going to use right away, otherwise broil until they bubble.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In pan mix water, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, food coloring and little salt.
Cook gently until thick.
Cool.	Pour cooled mixture over strawberries that have been placed in pie shell.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from turkey and open the turkey as flat as possible.
Combine herbs with oil.
Spread 1/2 the mixture over the inside of the turkey.
Reroll.
Spread the other half over the outside.
Wrap firmly in Saran Wrap, then put mesh back on.
Pierce in 2 or 3 places with a fork.
Place roast on a microwave-safe cooking rack over a baking dish.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes. Turn roast over, then microwave at 50% for 30 minutes, turning roast at 10 minute intervals until roast registers 170° in several places.
Remove from oven and let stand, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: tequila diablo
directions: In a blender or food processor, puree the pepper with the tomato vegetable juice; add the tequila, the lime juice and salt to taste and blend the mixture well.
Transfer the mixture to a pitcher and chill it for 30 minutes.
Pour the mixture into chilled tall glasses filled with ice cubes and decorate with lime wedges.
Makes 4 drinks.

title: dianne's coconut pie(microwave)
directions: Heat
milk
minutes on High.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg yolks, beaten.
Add to milk.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes until thickens (consistency of pudding).
Add coconut, butter
and vanilla.
Pour
into
cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue made from the 3 egg whites.
Brown in oven.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Add ground round to water in a 4-quart pot.
Stir until separates to a fine texture.
Boil slowly for 1/2 hour.
Add all other ingredients; stir to blend.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 3 hours.
The last hour, cover pot. When desired consistency is reached, chili should be refrigerated overnight so that fat can be lifted from top before reheating.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Will keep for a week.

title: chicken royale
directions: Place chicken breasts with skin side down on a work surface; pound lightly with a meat mallet to an even thickness for stuffing.
Combine bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, 2 tablespoons butter, water and parsley.
Place about 1/3 cup stuffing on each breast; fold in half.
Secure with toothpicks.
Combine flour and paprika; coat chicken.
Place, skewered side down, in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: low-fat pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar and applesauce; add eggs, water, flour, soda and cinnamon and salt.
Beat in pumpkin.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix together oatmeal, sugar, salt and flour.
Add melted butter, egg and vanilla.
Spoon onto cookie sheet (lined with foil) about 2 inches apart.
Cook 6 or 7 minutes at 375°.
Let cookies completely cool before removing from foil.
Yield: approximately 225 cookies.

title: grandpa oney's butter beans
directions: Shell fresh butter beans, wash and cook gently in simmering water, salted to taste, until beans are tender.
During the last few minutes of cooking, when water has nearly all cooked away, add ham strips or the drippings from cooked bacon.
Serve with crisp bacon strips as a garnish.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Saute sausage until done and crumbly.
Drain off fat.
Add cheese and melt.
Add oregano, catsup, A.1. sauce and salt.
Mix well.
Spread on bread generously.
Put pizza sauce on top of each.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze, then put in plastic bags and store in freezer.
Will keep well.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, until bubbly.
Good!

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into quart jar.
Put lid on and refrigerate until ready to use.
Good on spareribs, chicken or sausage.
Also in meat loaf or hamburger patties.
Do not cook, just blend and refrigerate.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: turkey chili macaroni
directions: Pour oil in large soup kettle and heat.
Add turkey to hot oil and stir.
Add celery and onion; stir mixture until no pink appears on turkey.
Add broth and cook covered until celery and onions are tender.
Drain this mixture into a large bowl.
Bring liquid to boil again.
You may add the liquid from 2 cans red kidney beans.
Add macaroni to boiling liquid and cook until tender (you may have to add additional liquid).
When macaroni is tender, add turkey/onion/celery mixture, kidney beans, spaghetti sauce, chili powder, garlic salt and water to this.
Heat and serve.
Can freeze in containers.

title: cherry cake squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add lemon extract.
Mix well.
Add flour a little at a time.
Use a jelly roll pan; grease and flour.
Spread dough in pan; mark off squares.
Add 1 tablespoon filling in the middle of each square.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: collard greens
directions: Place bacon in large heavy kettle.
Brown carefully.
Add 1 cup water to hot kettle.
Put in collards (that have been washed and torn from large stems).
Turn burner to lowest heat (not simmer).
Cook 1 hour.
Add about 1 1/2 cups water before putting lid on to cook.

title: mama's 1,2,3,4 cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder, sifting twice.
Add alternately with milk until mixed well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into Bundt pan or tube pan greased with Baker's Joy and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place stewed chicken, cut into pieces, in bottom of baking dish.
Heat cream of chicken soup (or cream of celery soup) with chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.

title: christmas salad
directions: Cut onion and pepper into squares.
Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Mix all together in a bowl. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Add dressing at serving time.

title: strawberries
directions: Add milk and vanilla to dry ingredients and stir well. Refrigerate one hour.
Shape into strawberries and roll in red sugar.
Dip stem end into green sugar.
(Colored sugars may be made by putting a few drops of food coloring in jar with sugar. Shake well.
Put on waxed paper to dry.)

title: grandma's chili
directions: Saute chopped beef with salt and pepper; drain and set aside. Saute onions in about 4 tablespoons vegetable oil in a large frying pan until tender.
Add kidney beans, catsup, molasses, garlic powder and meat which has been crumbled.
Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
A little water may be added.
A good hearty main dish served over cooked wide noodles and one or two other vegetables.

title: charlotte redwine's pound cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and Crisco together.
Add small amounts of milk and flour, alternating between the two, until well blended with butter mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavorings and remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: In saucepan, bring milk, rice and raisins to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine/butter until melted.
Combine nonfat dry milk powder, sugar and salt.
Stir in water and vanilla, mixing until powdered milk dissolves.
Stir in beaten eggs.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream
cheese and cottage cheese, then mix in seasoning packet.
Spread mixture on flat serving trays.
Spread taco sauce over mixture.
Next, layer onion, cheese and lettuce, then place tomatoes on top.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with your favorite crackers!
Serves 10 to 15.

title: mints
directions: Cream the cheese.
Add sugar, flavoring and food coloring. Dough should be very stiff.
If not stiff, add more sugar.
Roll about 1/2 teaspoon of mixture in palm.
Drop it in granulated sugar.
Press it in mold and pop out.
Makes about 80.

title: easy spice cake
directions: Follow directions for mixing cake on box.
Add spices while beating cake.
Bake as directed on box.

title: spicy carrots
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan and cover with water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and keep warm.
In the same pan, melt butter; stir in the sugar, horseradish and parsley.
Add the carrots, salt and pepper, stir gently to coat.
Makes 5 servings.

title: orange gelatin mold
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
While hot, add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Mix in until dissolved.
Chill until syrupy. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Combine flour and salt.
Add half of flour to cheese mixture; mix well, then add remaining flour and mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until pastry is easily handled. Roll out on lightly floured board.
Bake at 450° about 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before filling.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Strain macaroni; run cold water on, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, in one layer in open roasting pan.
In medium bowl, mix apricot preserves, Russian dressing and onion soup mix; pour over chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is fork tender, basting with sauce in pan occasionally during baking. While chicken is baking, prepare rice as label directs.
Stir parsley into cooked rice.
Serve chicken with sauce and rice. Makes 8 servings.

title: fudge walnut brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place sliced onions in bottom of crock-pot.
Add chicken pieces, minced garlic, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, herbs and white wine.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high 2 1/4 to 4 hours.
Serve chicken pieces with sauce over hot buttered spaghetti or noodles.

title: the sit sandwich
directions: Cut loaf of bread in half horizontally and hollow out soft bread from both halves, leaving shell 3/4-inch thick.
In small bowl, combine artichoke liquid with mayonnaise and spread over both halves of bread.
In bottom half, layer ingredients until mounded high.
Be sure to begin and end with tomatoes and put some in the middle.
Place top half of bread over mound of ingredients. Wrap entire loaf well with plastic wrap.
This can be assembled up to 8 hours before serving, but should be assembled at least 2 hours before serving.
(Keep refrigerated.)

title: shrimp and crab dip
directions: Heat soup with cream cheese.
Soften gelatin in cold water and add soup mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into gelatin mold and chill until firm.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Cover and chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: jello whipped pie
directions: Make jello; let thicken.
Add to thawed whipped topping.
Mix until well blended.
Put in pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight. Can substitute cherry jello.
Garnish with strawberries or cherries.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Set oven at 450° to preheat.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, margarine, shortening, egg yolks and soda (dissolved in buttermilk).
Add flour, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in egg whites with wire beater gently.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before adding icing.

title: special sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a small bowl. Stir well. Place sauce in a covered container and refrigerate for several hours, or overnight. so that the flavors blend. Stir the sauce a couple of times as it chills.

title: tourtiere(meat pie)
directions: Cover meat and onions with water.
Cook, uncovered, on medium-high until the water evaporates and down to the fat. Drain.
Add spices and potatoes; crush 4 saltines and add to it (this absorbs the fat).
Cool; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with pastry; prick to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce oven to 350° and bake until crust is light brown.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Boil until really soft.
Mash, then add flour, oleo, eggs, vanilla, sugar and milk.
Make sure they are soupy.
If not, add more milk.
Bake in 400° oven 1/2 hour.
Add marshmallows on top. Put in oven to brown for a few minutes.

title: mother's indian pudding
directions: Heat milk and pour in corn meal slowly.
Add sugar, eggs, butter and nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and toss stuffing, margarine and water lightly and put half into a buttered 12 x 5-inch casserole.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, green onion tops, mayonnaise and salt thoroughly and put in casserole over the first layer.
Top with other half of bread mixture.

title: pear brownies
directions: Mix
together
and
pour
into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: christmas cookie bars
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour on top of melted oleo the remaining ingredients in order listed. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over oats; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in sugars and margarine, add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together and beat into mixture.
Stir in 1/2 of chocolate chips.
Pour the batter in a greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle rest of chocolate chips and walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Easy and excellent.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken with additional celery and onion in the water. Add all ingredients and mix well.
Can be frozen.
Makes 5 to 6 cups.
If served on crisp lettuce, sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into precooked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 375° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Middle must be set to be done.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Pour into individual dishes. Serve with a teaspoon of lite Cool Whip on top.

title: caramel pie
directions: Caramelize sugar to medium brown.
Dissolve with boiling water.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Combine brown sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Add some of the boiling milk and blend well. Return to saucepan and cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue and brown at 400° to a light brown.

title: coleslaw with shrimp and tarragon
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and tarragon in large bowl. Whisk to blend.
Mix in cabbage, carrots and onion.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Mix in shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes or up to 4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Stir in nuts and chips. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; blend well. Press into pie dish. Bake at 350° until browned.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, salt and soda.
Add milk, corn, margarine and eggs. Meanwhile, brown beef with onion and jalapenos; pour off fat. Grease large skillet.
Pour half of batter into skillet.
Top with meat mixture, then cheese.
Pour remaining batter over cheese. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: easy delicious roast
directions: Prepare au jus sauce and gravy mix, adding a little extra water.
Heat until boiling.
Pour gravy mixture in crock-pot and add roast.
Cook on high until roast is tender.
Makes a delicious roast with its own gravy.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat 1 minute.
Stir-fry chicken in two batches until browned.
Remove from skillet and remove skillet from heat.
Spray skillet with cooking spray.
Add vegetables and stir-fry until tender crisp. Add soup, water, soy sauce and ginger; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into casserole dish.
Top with additional crushed chips to cover top.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with hot biscuits and a tossed salad for a quick supper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into thin slices and brown in hot oil in a skillet. Remove meat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until onion is golden. Add the remaining ingredients and meat.
Simmer until done. Lastly, add the thickening and the sour cream.
Serve over rice or cooked noodles.

title: pickled cucumbers
directions: Alternate onions, bell pepper and cucumbers in a gallon jar. Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, turmeric and mustard seed; bring to a boil and pour over pickles.
Refrigerate and mix often in a jar.

title: banana bread(low-fat)
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, applesauce, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
On low speed, add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Add mashed bananas.

title: *egg-lemon soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil. Add rice. Cook until tender, about 20 minutes. Remove broth from heat.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into baked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage rice
directions: Break up sausage; brown and drain well.
Mix with next 8 ingredients; place in casserole.
(At this point, it may be refrigerated for a day.)
When ready to bake, add bouillon. Bake, covered, for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8 as side dish.

title: sausage polenta
directions: Note:
You can use 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce instead of tomatoes, tomato paste and mushrooms.

title: michelle's taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put all ingredients in crock pot and simmer until cheese melts.

title: see's fudge
directions: In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients.
In large pan (not skillet) combine milk and sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil for 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over other ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 or 12 x 1-inch pan.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, sour milk and vanilla.
Blend in cocoa, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda, cloves and zucchini.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Mix chicken, celery, croutons, Miracle Whip, milk, onion and Swiss cheese.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake in a 2-quart baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Favorite dish at gatherings! Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter. Add onion and cook until brown. Add remaining ingredients and cook 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 6.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut okra into 1/2 pieces.
Heat a frying pan with cooking oil. Season with your favorite seasonings.
Scramble the egg in bowl. Place cut okra in the egg mixture and make sure each piece is covered.
Then place in flour; remove when completely covered. Drop the battered pieces of okra in hot grease and cook until brown.
When brown, remove and place on a paper towel to drain. Can be served with your favorite meat.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add next 6 ingredients, tomatoes and tomato paste. Add 1/2 cup water if too thick. Cook and stir for 45 minutes. Cook noodles; drain and rinse in cold water. Combine cottage cheese and next 4 ingredients plus Parmesan cheese. Layer in 9 x 13 pan the noodles, meat mixture, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese. Continue until the pan is full. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan balls(mexican wedding cookies)
directions: Beat butter with mixer, add flour, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into 1 inch balls. Place on ungreased
cookie pan.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly. Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Put in loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Delicious.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Mix ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pan 25 minutes, then invert onto serving plate.
Prick top with fork, then spoon and brush Rum Glaze evenly over cake.
When cake is cooled, drizzle Chocolate Glaze over cake.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons chopped nuts.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, spices and onion.
Shape into 12 to 16 meatballs.
Stir together wet ingredients.
Pour over raw meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: soup mix
directions: Cook butter beans. Cut kernels from corn. Dice onions. Slice okra. Chop peppers. Combine all ingredients. Bring to a rolling boil. Seal in jars. Makes 8 quarts.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in softened ice cream.
Pour into shell.
Freeze until firm.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Spread crescents out and pinch seams together.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Mix Miracle Whip, cream cheese and dressing; spread over crust.
Pour veggies (mixed together) on top and press into cream mixture.
Chill and cut into bars.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Blend all ingredients in order mentioned and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spicy banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and oil.
Blend the eggs and bananas well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to banana mixture.
Add the nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry eight tortillas in frying pan with 1 tablespoon of oil until soft.
Roll chicken, cheese and onions into tortillas.
Mix sour cream, soup and a little milk.
Pour a little mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in the enchiladas and pour the rest of the mixture on top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic frittata
directions: Beat together eggs, milk and Parmesan cheese; set aside.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter and saute garlic, onion, sausage and potatoes for about 5 minutes or until tender. Reduce heat to medium.
Pour egg mixture into pan and cook, without stirring, until eggs are almost set.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of frittata.
Let cook on top of stove for about 1 more minute.
Place pan under broiler and broil about 6 inches from heat until top is bubbly and slightly browned.
Cut in wedges to serve.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Cover with cold salt water (1
cup
salt per gallon).
Let set 7 days.
If scum forms, skim and add more salt.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In Dutch oven, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to medium -low; simmer 30 minutes.
Remove spices; discard.
Serve hot.
Yields twenty one cup servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except chickens).
Put chickens in deep baking pan and pour sauce over.
Cover and bake at 375° for 2 hours, basting every 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato and onion slices. Place in a casserole dish.
Arrange tomato and onion slices on top of beans.
Bake
in 375° oven for 35 minutes.	Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: salmon mold
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into ball and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 6-quart freezer. Super delicious and so easy to make.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; put into baking dish.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese and sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot corn
directions: Mix corn, cream cheese and jalapenos (use at least 3 whole ones).
Put into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend together creamed corn, egg yolks, cornstarch, sugar and milk.
Fold in slightly beaten egg whites.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for approximately 80 minutes, until brown.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend together sugar and flour, then stir into eggs with remaining ingredients.
Turn into two greased 9-inch pie pans (no crust).
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until coconut is browned and pie is firm.

title: peanut butter crispies(make in microwave oven)
directions: Put sugar and syrup in a microwave-safe dish and stir to mix. Cook on High 3 minutes.
Should be bubbling hard. Take out and add other ingredients.
Mix well and put in pan to cool.
Cut in squares.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix until smooth and pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Spread with butter while hot.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy stir-fry
directions: Spray a large skillet with the cooking spray until well coated. Brown meat in skillet and, if using ground beef, drain fat.
After browning, spray the meat with more Pam for more flavor.
Add 1 tablespoon of soy sauce and garlic salt while browning.
After meat is done, add your vegetables and simmer until all is well blended together.
Serve with cooked rice.
Preparation time is 30 minutes.

title: midwest meat loaf
directions: Stir Velveeta, milk and mustard in small saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Reserve 3/4 c. cheese for sauce.
Mix remaining ingredients and cheese in large bowl until blended. Shape into
loaf pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Pour cheese over and serve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring water to boil and add bouillon cubes, garlic powder and pepper.
Add onion, celery, carrots and cabbage.
Boil gently until vegetables are tender; add tomatoes.
Boil gently just until heated through.
Contains 48 calories per cup serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add flour and eggs. Beat well. Add buttermilk and flavoring. Pour into 9 inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until brown on top. Makes two small pies or one large deep dish pie.

title: broiled salmon steaks
directions: Soak fillets in Italian dressing for 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.
Place fish steaks on gas or charcoal grill.
Cook each side until flaky.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: stromboli
directions: Saute sausage, onion and bell pepper.
Drain well.
Spread thawed dough into large rectangle.
Layer ingredients into a large pile on top of bread.
Pull sides and seal.
(It will be large and bulky.)
Roll into an oiled pan or cookie sheet seam side down. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no egg or milk chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Add cool water, oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: slungarian
directions: Roll hamburger into meatballs.
Combine tomato paste with water in a large saucepan until a sauce mixture appears.
Place meatballs and potatoes "which need to be diced" along with diced onion into sauce.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer until potatoes are tender.
Salt and pepper as desired.

title: ancestral recipe for applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly oil a 9 x 9-inch cake pan. Measure applesauce into mixing bowl.
Add oil and sugar.
Measure out flour.
Add spices and soda; stir to mix, then add to applesauce mixture.
Stir well.
Add chocolate chips and raisins and stir some more.
Scrape into cake pan.
Lick spoon.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(This cake keeps well even if not eaten right away.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine in the order given. Pour into a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with 1 stick oleo, thinly sliced.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Spread a very thin layer of cream cheese on ham slices.
Roll up.
Secure each roll with toothpick.
Place in freezer until firm (not frozen).
Slice in 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: crisp cuke slices
directions: Mix cukes, white onions, garlic cloves or chips and salt. Cover with ice and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine the sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar; heat to boiling.
Add cukes and heat to boiling.
Pack in pints jars. Process in hot water for 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend filling ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Filling should appear slightly less set in center than around edge.

title: low-fat chicken alfredo
directions: In saucepan over low heat, blend flour, liquid Butter Buds, skim milk and chicken broth.
Add minced garlic, salt and pepper. Continue to cook over low heat stirring constantly until the sauce thickens.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Combine sauce with chicken and mushrooms.
Fold into cooked pasta.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and dot the top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice in boiler.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and chill until firm.

title: quicky cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Pour in batter.
Add fruit; do not stir. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: mock chicken pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put over low flame until simmering.
Remove from heat and place in casserole dish.
Place biscuits over top. Bake at 375° until biscuits are a golden brown.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Add all ingredients to blender.
Blend several seconds.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch pie dish or two 8-inch pans. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a rolling boil. Turn off heat. Add tea bags and let stand 5 minutes. Squeeze excess water out of tea bags and remove. Add orange juice and lemon juice. Serve hot.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir into stuffing.
Add egg and sausage and blend thoroughly.
Chill for abut 1 hour for easier handling; then shape into small oblongs, about the size of pecans.
Cut bacon strips into thirds, crosswise. Wrap one piece of bacon around dressing mixture and fasten with wooden picks.
Place on rack in shallow pan and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown and crisp, turning at halfway point.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.
May be made the day before baking; also freezes well before baking.
Makes about 36 appetizers.

title: devilished good dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Bake in loaf pan for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry bread
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and almond extract.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with strawberries to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into strawberry mixture.
Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with greased wax paper.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 15 minutes on rack. Remove from pan and cool.
Makes one loaf.
Bread freezes well and also makes delicious toast.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; add soup and cheese.
Saute onion in margarine. Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini custard pie
directions: Blend all in blender and pour in pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° and then 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Line pie crust with sliced strawberries.
Cook other ingredients until thick and clear, adding food color last.
Pour mixture over berries.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream after cooled.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 350.

title: muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of about 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Makes about 1 dozen muffins.

title: st. patrick's day cupcakes
directions: Mix flour, pudding mix, chocolate pieces, sugar and baking powder.
Combine eggs, milk and extract; stir into first mixture, just until combined.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.
Frost with 1/2 can cream cheese frosting.
Sprinkle with green colored sugar.

title: marinated green beans and potatoes
directions: Cook, drain and cool potatoes and beans.
Mix all other ingredients in a jar; shake well.
Pour over vegetables for at least 1 hour (better overnight).

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Baker's Joy.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan and set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each quarter in sugar mixture and layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and melted butter.
Pour over dough.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese and egg casserole
directions: Remove crust from 15 slices of bread.
Butter the slices, cube and put 7 slices in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Sprinkle cubes with 2 cups grated cheese.
Layer remaining bread (cubed).

title: german potato salad
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove; set aside. Cook onion in 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings until done.
Stir in flour, mix well.
Add water and vinegar; cook until slightly thickened.
Add sugar and cook until sugar dissolves.
Crumble bacon and add to mixture with potatoes.
Heat, stirring lightly to coat the potatoes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hayden salad
directions: Grind together the tomatoes, cabbage, onions and green peppers. Add salt and let set for 2 hours.

title: oatmeal bread(bread machine)
directions: `Put in bread pan in order given.
Select white bread setting. Bake according to bread machine directions.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: In a very large bowl, mix dry ingredients, add eggs, milk and oil.
Mix well.
(Add nuts, dates or extra raisins if desired.) Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store extra batter in refrigerator.
Date it and it will be good for six weeks.
Baked muffins also freeze well.
Makes a lot.

title: buckaroo beans
directions: Boil beans in water for 2 minutes.
Cover and remove from fire.
Let stand for 1 hour, then return to stove.
Add all remaining ingredients, except salt; simmer for 3 1/2 hours.
Add salt to taste.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and shape into loaf.
Pour one can of tomato paste and one can of water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: "lizzies"(fruit cake cookies)
directions: Cream margarine, gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with soda and spices.
Add to margarine mixture.
Soak raisins in bourbon at least one hour to plump; then add to margarine mixture, along with nuts and fruit.
Drop from teaspoon on buttered cookie sheets. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Can be frozen.
Makes 120.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, egg and pineapple.
Add soda, vanilla, chips and then flour.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt emma's hot german potato salad
directions: In a covered pan, cook potatoes until tender.
Drain well.
In mixing bowl, mash potatoes with old fashioned masher.
Sprinkle potatoes with sugar and vinegar.
Add celery, onions, sweet relish, salt and parsley flakes to the potatoes.
Stir the mixture to combine with potatoes.
Add mayonnaise or dressing in potato mixture.
Carefully fold in 2 of the boiled eggs after cutting them into medium size pieces.
Slice the other 2 eggs into 1/2-inch slices and place over finished prepared salad.
Sprinkle paprika over top and serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into rolls.
Freeze cookie rolls.
Remove from freezer.
Slice real thin.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no fail wheat bread
directions: Mix together
first
ingredients.
Add hot water and honey. Beat
200 strokes.
Add remaining flour.
Mix together and let rise 30 to 60 minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Form into 40 meatballs;
brown
in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Cover, cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Drain.
Heat for 10-20 minutes until sauce thickens, stirring occasionally.

title: microwaved cheese cake
directions: In an 8-inch round cake dish, place butter.
Put microwave at 1 3/4 minutes to melt.
Stir in crumbs and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Press mixture on bottom and side of dish.

title: jambalaya
directions: Season and brown chicken in oil. Add sausage to pot and saute with chicken. Remove from pot. Add heaping tablespoonful of brown sugar to hot oil and caramelize. Make a roux or use Kitchen Bouquet. For red jambalaya, add paprika for color. Saut onions, celery, green peppers and garlic to the tenderness that you desire. Return chicken and sausage to pot. Add liquid and Joe's Stuff and bring to a boil. If using Kitchen Bouquet for brown jambalaya, add 1 to 2 tablespoons. For red jambalaya, add approximately 1/4 cup paprika and you may want to use 1/2 stock and tomato juice or V-8 for your liquid. Add rice and return to boil. Cover and reduce heat to simmer. Cook 25 minutes. After 10 minutes of cooking, remove and turn rice after 10 minutes of cooking. Add green onions and tomatoes.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: About 45 Minutes Before Serving:

Cut each chicken breast half lengthwise in half, then cut crosswise into 1/4-inch thick strips. In 4-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken strips just until they lose pink color throughout, stirring frequently. With slotted spoon, remove chicken to bowl and set aside.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes good.
Cut in rings with potato peel left on potatoes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan (glass or aluminum).
Cut onion up in rings.
Break apart and place over potatoes (you can do this by layers if you want).
Then cut up butter in pieces; place on potatoes and onion.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until desired tenderness.

title: white chocolate pretzels
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave or double boiler.
With tongs, dip pretzels, one at a time, in chocolate.
Let excess chocolate run off back into pan.
Place dipped pretzels on waxed paper to cool; chill to harden slightly.
Melt the semi-sweet chocolate; cool several minutes.
Using a pastry bag with small round plastic tip (or a plastic bag with the tip snipped off or a large spoon), drizzle dark chocolate squiggles over coated pretzels.
Immediately sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Chill.

title: laurie's party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 30 minutes.
Serve with bite-sized tortilla chips.

title: swiss broccoli casserole
directions: Thoroughly combine soup and milk.
Arrange broccoli in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer eggs, 1/2 can French fried onions, soup mixture and cheese over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: orange sherbet mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in orange sherbet. When jello is about jelled, fold in mandarin oranges and whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups of flour, the sugar, shortening, salt and yeast in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add water, milk and egg.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn on floured surface and knead until smooth, 5 minutes.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix reserved juice and pudding.
Mix in a bowl.
Stir in pineapple, bananas, oranges, cherries, coconut and nuts.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in coconut and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Be sure to beat well the first 5 ingredients.)

title: pepper dish
directions: Dice potatoes, green peppers and onion.
Brown beef.
Drain. Return to skillet.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Add diced food to skillet.
Add tomatoes, cut up.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked. Layer top with cheese.
When melted, stir thoroughly.

title: beef salami
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 2 rolls.
Wrap in foil; twist ends well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Do not remove foil.
Place in pan; cover with water.
Boil for 60 minutes. Punch holes in foil to drain.
Re-wrap and refrigerate.
Serve cold; slice thin.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix raisin bran, flour, soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl. Add
Crisco,
eggs	and
buttermilk to dry ingredients. Add extra raisins
if
desired.
Store
in
covered
bowl
in refrigerator. Do not stir again.	Bake in greased muffin tins for 20
minutes at 400°.
Mix will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Use as you need it!!

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese on high speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Add onion, horseradish, Worcestershire, salt and celery salt.
Blend thoroughly.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes to blend flavor. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: rose potpourri
directions: Mix together in glass container, tightly covered, for 2 to 4 weeks.
Shake the container daily.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add frozen coconut and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.
Bake according to directions.
While cake is baking, mix evaporated milk, sugar, vanilla and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring.
Stir until dissolved and add enough water to make two cups.
Punch holes every inch in cake with toothpick.
Spoon the two cups of liquid over cake while hot.
Cool completely.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Add shortening, mix with fork. Add unbeaten eggs and flavoring. Mix well. Roll out very thin. Cut and bake. Decorate if desired. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Take one piece of chicken, ham and cheese in order; roll up and close with toothpick.
Coat in mixture of flour and paprika. Cook in butter until brown.
Add wine and bouillon cube.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet (remove toothpick).
Blend cornstarch and cream in skillet; stir until smooth and thick.
Pour over chicken on platter and serve hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is a good vegetable for any meal, but is especially good with roast pork.

title: surrey house catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coarsely grind crackers and peanuts together.
Place in mixing bowl and stir in 2 tablespoons melted butter.
In separate bowl, mix vinegar, honey and mustard together.
Take catfish fillet, skin side down, and spread evenly over the fillet the mustard sauce.
Coat the entire fillet with cracker and peanut crumbs.
Drizzle remaining 2 tablespoons butter over the crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes, covered.
Finish, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes to allow crumbs to brown.
Best served with mild flavored rice.

title: rick's favorite hamburgers
directions: With the ground beef on the bottom of a large bowl, pour remaining ingredients in and use a strong utensil to combine. When it's combined well enough to handle, "knead" the hamburger mix a little more to make sure all the garlic and egg is worked through all the meat. Make patties and for best results, BARBECUE the hamburgers on a PREHEATED grill (medium-high heat). Cook 8 minutes per side.

title: western manapua
directions: Brown together first 3 ingredients.
Drain off fat.
Separate the packages of crescent rolls.
Unroll carefully and cut the four sheets into fourths.
Place 1 teaspoon filling into the tiny triangle piece and pinch together to close.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: trash
directions: Mix cereal, pretzels and nuts in large bowl.
Melt chocolate and pour over the cereal mixture.
Stir and lay out on wax paper in a thin layer.

title: crumb apple pie
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, salt and butter; blend until crumbly and set aside. Combine apples, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon and toss gently to coat apples. Spoon apple mixture into chilled crust. Sprinkle crumb topping over apples. Wrap foil around edge of crust. Bake at 350° until apples are tender, about 1 hour. Remove foil after first 30 minutes of baking.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Spread 1/2 of the apricot preserves onto each unbaked pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife will slide in and come out clean. Cool on racks, then refrigerate.

title: onion-potato bake
directions: Layer half the potatoes and half the onions in a greased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper.
Combine milk, pimiento and parsley; spoon half the mixture over onion-potato layer; repeat layers.
Cover.

title: rolls
directions: Mix and let rise until double in size.
Knead and roll (refrigerate if desired).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: virginia spoonbread
directions: Mix well, pour into baking dish.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: indian pudding
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place 3 cups milk in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Scald milk, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
Add raisins.
Place cornmeal in small mixing bowl, stir in 1 cup milk. Add to milk in pan, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Stir in molasses, salt, sugar, ginger, nutmeg and butter.
Stir well to blend.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole dish and grease well with butter.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add next 5 ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in rhubarb.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Cream cheese and jello together in mixer.
Pour boiling water on to dissolve; cool.
Put in refrigerator for a time.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip; fold in until mixed together.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour. Add coconut, then add it all to the batter.
Cook in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Put 1 cup fresh orange juice on low heat; pour over cake as soon as it is removed from the oven.
Let stand in pan overnight or for several hours.

title: elephant stew
directions: Clean elephant and rabbits.
Cut into bite size pieces; make enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire at 465° for 4 weeks.
At end of second week, add onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve 38,000; if more are expected, add two more rabbits.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Into medium bowl sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mix resembles coarse crumbs.
Make well in center; pour in milk all at once. Stir with fork just until blended.
Drop by tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 14 to 16.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add can of crushed pineapple. Follow with cherry pie filling and the box of yellow cake mix. Slice sticks of butter over top and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Melt next 2 ingredients in double boiler. Roll first ingredients and dip in melted ingredients. Place on foil and cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute in onion.
Add all other ingredients except onion rings.
Mix together and pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° until really bubbly on top.
Top with onion rings for last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: mixed greens and granny smith apples
directions: Wash and drain salad greens, toss sliced apples, blue cheese and walnuts with salad greens in a large bowl.
Pour raspberry dressing over the salad to taste.
Serve on chilled salad plates.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix butter, broccoli and onion and cook in microwave for 7 1/2 minutes.
Then mix cooked rice, mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz. Cook, uncovered, in microwave for 7 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix paste and spices together.
Add onions and cheese.
Then add the meat.
Spread on hamburger bun halves and broil for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: surprise cake
directions: Combine butter, salt, eggs, milk, vanilla and sugar.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add mincemeat that has been stirred until smooth.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: no cal soup
directions: Mix and cook for 2 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix by hand only. Add bananas and nuts.
Mix again.
Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan for one hour and 5 minutes.

title: egg souffle
directions: Mix egg and milk; add salt and dry mustard.
Butter bread, remove crusts and cube.
Toss together with cheese.
Place bread and cheese in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour egg-milk mixture over.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian egg bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: mediterranean salad with balsamic vinaigrette(serves 8)
directions: Drain salmon.
Wash, peel and slice cucumbers.
Wash, core and roughly chop tomatoes. Crumble cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and roll in chopped pecans.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in a covered container. To serve, put	1/3
to
1/2 cup of mixture in a cup.
Fill cup with hot water.	Stir.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut cookie dough in 1/4-inch slices. Arrange overlapping in 13-inch pizza pan.
Press edges to seal. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen cookie dough. Allow to finish cooling.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture. Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meat roll-ups
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl and grate onion into it.
Mix in lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salad dressing, salt and pepper. Mix well.
(An electric mixer may be used).
Cut both bolognas into 3 strips per slice.
Spread with 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Roll strips and fasten with a toothpick.
Refrigerate until served.
Leftover cream cheese mixture makes a great chip dip too.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
For into round ball; roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Take skin off of chicken; wash and dry the chicken well.
Dip chicken into milk.
Mix cornflakes with pepper.
Roll chicken in crumbs.
Let chicken stand a few minutes.
Spread oil in large baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken satay
directions: Marinate chicken mixture for 24 hours. Drain marinade and cook chicken. Serve with Coconut-Peanut Sauce.

title: curried ham salad
directions: Mix ham, pineapple, celery, onions and raisins in medium glass bowl. Stir curry powder into mayonnaise; fold into ham mixture. Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 4 hours but no longer than 48 hours.
Stir and sprinkle with toasted coconut, if desired.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes covered.

title: dove casserole
directions: Cover the first 4 ingredients with water.
Boil until doves are tender.
Debone doves and set aside.
Brown 2 medium finely chopped onions in 1 stick butter.
Add 1 cup uncooked rice and brown.
Mix 2 cans of onion soup, 2 small cans mushrooms, 1 small (4 ounce) jar pimento and deboned doves.
Add this mixture to browned rice and place in casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°. Turn off oven and let stand 10 minutes in oven.

title: hot cheese loaf
directions: Carefully slice top off bread loaf; remove bread from center of loaf in square chunks.
Combine all remaining ingredients. Fill hollowed loaf with cheese mixture.
Place top slice on loaf and wrap in foil.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.
Serve warm with toasted or untoasted bread squares, chips or crackers.
(Chop beef, chiles, pimentos and onions in food processor.)

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and saute onions. Combine bacon, onions and potatoes.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Add whole and creamed corn.
Rinse cans.
Simmer until vegetables are well done.
Add salt, pepper and parsley to taste.
Just before serving, add evaporated milk.
Heat and serve.

title: tasty brown rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill 1 or 2 hours before serving.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ham and pork.
Add milk and cracker crumbs.
Form into 24 balls (2-inches in diameter).
Place in shallow baking pan.
Pour Brown Sugar Sauce over meatballs and bake in 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in mixture, then place on plate to cool.

title: edna's apricot sticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
In large mixer bowl (set at medium or cream), beat shortening with 1/2 cup sugar and lemon rind until very light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour mixture, mixing well.
Over bottom of pan, pat dough in even layer.
Cover with apricot jam.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Melt margarine and spoon over top of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.

title: lemon chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix and margarine and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and cream cheese and pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: corned beef toast
directions: Melt shortening, stir in flour until lightly browned and add water or milk.
Stir until smooth and slightly thickened.
Add corned beef, stirring until hot and bubbly.
Cover toast and serve.

title: cauliflower-broccoli dish
directions: All vegetables must be fresh, frozen will not work.
Steam or blanche vegetables and put in a casserole dish.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add melted butter and mix with fork. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in pastry shell. Sprinkle chopped pecans evenly on top.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: coconut balls
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add chopped nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix and form into balls. Roll in coconut and powdered sugar.

title: buttermilk frosting
directions: Cook
all ingredients until soft ball stage over medium heat.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
Mix. Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry mixture and stir only until moistened.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan or in a 10-inch heavy skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bread is a golden brown and tests done.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple custard
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and flour.
Add vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir in milk and applesauce.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage-tomato skillet
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover, bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring once.
Uncover and simmer a few minutes to reduce liquid.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheerwine ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well and finish filling your freezer with plain milk.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together and pour into greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 325° until tested with toothpick and it comes out clean.

title: shredded refrigerator slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onion in bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, celery seed and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Pour over layers.
Chill for up to 3 days.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Cook first three ingredients until rice is done; stir several times.
In separate bowl beat egg whites; add milk and vanilla. Beat again.
Add this mixture to cooked rice, stirring slowly as you add.
Bring to to a fast boil; turn off.
Pour into large bowl.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Make a day ahead.

title: hot dog roll-ups
directions: Cut a lengthwise slit in each hot dog; fill with a strip of cheese and about 1/2 teaspoon bacon.
Separate crescent dough into eight triangles.
Place a hot dog on the wide end of each triangle; roll toward the point.
Place cheese side up on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add Karo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all together and pour into a 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Put in pie crust and bake 55 minutes in 425° oven.
It is done if inserted knife comes out clean.
Can use carrots in place of squash.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix well the first 9 ingredients.
Sift together flour and soda.
Stir into mixture with a spoon.
Refrigerate dough for several hours.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream together	shortening
and
sugar;
add 1 egg at a time, beating
well
after
each	addition.
Sift together dry ingredients;
add
alternately
with
buttermilk.
Add vanilla and blend
well.
Pour half the batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch
tube
pan;
add
chocolate syrup to remaining batter. Mix;
pour chocolate mixture over top of other batter and fold
in gently
with spatula for marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool and frost as desired.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 3 minutes.
Prick with fork, bake 5 minutes longer and let cool.
Cook sausage until browned; drain. Combine eggs, milk and seasonings in a medium mixing bowl.
Mix lightly.
Stir in sausage.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup cheese over pastry shell; top with sausage mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 3/4 cup cheese and bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: zucchini relish
directions: You will need 6 pint canning jars, lids and rings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Use on ribs, chicken, etc.

title: chicken in mushroom gravy
directions: Place chicken pieces in crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix wine and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms. Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).
Recipe may be doubled for 5-quart crock-pot.
Remove chicken and cook noodles in gravy for a good and easy meal.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt margarine, then add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Mix well and let boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Stir and let cool.
Drop on wax paper.

title: brownie nut pie
directions: Mix nuts and crumbs.
Beat egg whites and salt.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff but not dry.
Add vanilla.
Fold egg mixture into crumb mixture, folding thoroughly but gently.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Mix the drained vegetables, which have had the moisture squeezed out of them, with softened cream cheese and lemon juice. Add just enough mayonnaise to make a spreading consistency.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Heat milk until warm (not hot).
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until they melt.
Add marshmallows and pecans. Pour in buttered dish or pan.
Chill.

title: cucumber salad (1)
directions: Sprinkle salt over all and let set 1/2 hour.
Drain cucumbers.

title: parsley sauce
directions: See recipe for Brown Sauce.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Mix in Brown Sauce, parsley and lemon juice.
Add butter and season with salt and pepper to taste just before serving.

title: fresh fruit cake
directions: Pinch angel food cake into little pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take juice from Mandarin oranges and pineapple and add enough orange juice to make 3 cups; add pudding.
Cook, then cool.
Pour over cake, then place Mandarin oranges, pineapple, grapes, strawberries, bananas and kiwi and pour over pudding.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Follow directions on cake mix, then fill ice cream cones 2/3 full of batter.
Place cones filled with batter in cupcake tins and bake at 350° until done.
Cool, then top with frosting.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Empty cake mix into bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until mixture forms moist even crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mix for topping. Add to remaining crumb mixture, 1 egg; stir until blended.
Spoon into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press lightly to form an even layer.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until puffy.
Set aside.

title: great potato soup
directions: In Dutch oven or soup kettle, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, and 1 tsp. salt.
Bring to boil reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Do not drain.
Meanwhile, in saucepan, melt butter, whisk in flour and salt.
Cook 1 minute. Gradually stir in milk and cheese.
Cool until cheese is melted and mixture has thickened.
Fold in ham.
Stir into vegetables and broth.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat sugar and oleo. Add eggs and bananas; beat.
Mix in dry ingredients, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf or 3 small loaves.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in bowl and set aside.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water.
Put strawberries in hot gelatin and stir until melted.
Add crushed pineapple and stir well.
Pour into rectangular, flat dish and chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: brunch eggs sunny-side up
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, soup, onion and mustard.
Cook and stir until smooth and heated through.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese until melted.
Using two 10 x 6 x 2 1/2-inch baking dishes, pour 1 cup sauce into each.
Break eggs, one at a time, into baking dishes.
Carefully spoon remaining sauce around eggs.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: tuna turnovers
directions: In bowl knead cream cheese, flour and 6 tablespoons butter. Wrap and freeze for 30 minutes.
In skillet over medium heat in 2 tablespoons hot butter, cook vegetables until tender.
Remove from heat.
Tear bread in small pieces.
Add tuna and salt to cooked vegetables.
Roll 1/2 dough; cut crosswise into two squares. Spoon one-fourth tuna mixture onto half of each square.
Brush dough edges with some egg.
Fold dough diagonally over filling. With fork press edges together.
Cut slashes to vent steam. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Place on cookie sheet and cook in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: cheese dip
directions: Stir flour in butter.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Add seasonings, milk, cheese and 1 tablespoon catsup.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix together corn, flour, sugar, salt and pepper to taste, then eggs and cheese.
Heat the oil in a deep fat fryer to 360° or until a small cube of stale bread dropped into the oil turns golden in 50 seconds.

title: carrot salad
directions: Stir until mixed together then stir into salad.
Best if you keep in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, sugar, salt, egg yolks and juice. Blend all together.
Beat egg whites until stiff and foamy.
Fold into ingredients.
Cook over low heat and keep stirring until it thickens when it cools.
Fold in whip cream.
Serve over lime Jell-O with crushed pineapple in it.

title: meat ball soup
directions: Mix rice and ground beef.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Form into about 20 meat balls.
In large soup utensil, bring water and tomato juice to a boil.
Add 2 teaspoons salt, celery, onion and raw meat balls.
Boil slowly for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add tomatoes (cut up or diced) and bouillon cubes; simmer until hot (do not overcook).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Place 1/2 of crumbled cornbread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chopped onion, bell pepper and tomato together. Place on top of cornbread.
Sprinkle most of the crumbled bacon on top of vegetables.
Drain juice from pinto beans and pour over bacon.

title: deb's potato salad
directions: Cook white potatoes until done.
In a large bowl, combine mustard, vinegar, sugar, pepper, mayo, salad cubes and eggs; mix well.
Add paprika on top to add color.

title: squash pickles
directions: In large container, place squash, onions, green peppers and salt.
Cover with ice water and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain well. In saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar, mustard and celery seed. Bring syrup to a full boil, stirring often to dissolve sugar.
Add vegetables and return liquid to full boil.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and process for 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grate rind of 2 oranges.
Add gelatine dissolved in pineapple juice or water.
Mix all ingredients and let congeal.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator or you may freeze.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey and drain.
Add onion and garlic (bell pepper is optional).
Add tomatoes, sauce and paste.
Add spices to taste.
Cook until onion is done and sauce is very thick.

title: massengill's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and bring to a boil to thicken.

title: fried onion chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts.
Dip chicken in egg-milk mixture, then in onion rings.
Place in an 8-inch round glass dish; cover.
Cook in microwave on High for 6 1/2 to 10 minutes, rotating dish every 4 minutes.
Cut into bite size pieces before serving.
This dish can be assembled, but not cooked, ahead of time and store in the refrigerator until guests arrive.
Then just microwave and serve.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in round or square cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar until smooth. Stir in whipped topping.
Spread in crust.
Add 1 cup of milk to pudding mixes and beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
May garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts.

title: wassail drink
directions: One day I saw a sign that read "Heaven's Grocery Store".
As I got up a little closer, the door came open wide and when I came to myself, I was standing just inside.
I saw a host of angels, who were standing everywhere.
One handed me a basket and said, "my child, please shop with care".
Everything a Christian needed was in that grocery store.
And all you couldn't carry, you could come back for more.

title: baked stuffed onions
directions: In large saucepan, place onions, 1/2 teaspoon salt and enough water (cold) to cover; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until onions are tender.
Drain and let cool.
