With spoon, scoop out center of onions, leaving several outside layers as a shell.
Chop scooped out onion very fine; measure 2 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream soft butter with sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating well.
Combine flour and soda and add to mixture with sour cream. Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first
6 ingredients together, the add remaining ingredients.
Mix all well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (makes 2 loaves).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: veg dip
directions: Blend all together and serve with vegetables.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Stir chocolate in 1/4 cup water on low heat until melted. Cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, creaming well after each.
Add chocolate.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt, add alternately with milk to creamed mixture until well blended.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cookie crumble
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add chocolate bits.
Spread on cookie sheet (ungreased). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and break.
Do not overbake!

title: lemon ice
directions: Boil the water in a saucepan; stir in sugar until dissolved. Remove from heat and cool.
Add lemon juice and zest.
Pour mixture into a metal bowl and freeze.
When ready to serve, beat the ice until fluffy and scoop into lemon or lime "shells" or serve in small glass bowls or wine glasses.
Top with mint sprigs.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In large stock pot, melt margarine.
Add all seasonings and flour; cook while stirring until flour browns.
Add chicken and sausage; let simmer for 10 minutes.
Add water and shrimp; stir until smooth.
Add rice, crabmeat and hot sauce.
When rice is done, add okra and crab claws.
Let simmer for 1 hour and serve. Makes 25 servings.

title: bean soup supper
directions: Saute meat, onions and bell pepper.
Drain.
Combine with the rest of ingredients.
Simmer and serve.

title: ritz surprises
directions: Cook dates and milk until thick, stirring constantly.
Add nuts.
Spread generously on Ritz crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Watch closely.
Cool and frost with buttercream frosting. Makes 88 crackers.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat.
Add oleo and stir until melted. Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add vanilla.
Pour in a baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown meringue in a 350° oven.

title: quick lunch box cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts in a large bowl.
Blend well at low speed, 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Soak lasagna in hot water until soft and limp.
Brown hamburger meat with onion.

title: beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat in 2 tablespoons hot shortening, turning often.
Add 2 cups hot water and next 9 ingredients. Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: greek chicken
directions: In a 9-inch square baking pan, spread the olive oil.
Add 2 cloves of garlic and half of the lemon, then layer with half of the chicken.
Mix together in a separate bowl the spinach, Feta cheese, remaining garlic, oregano and parsley.
Layer this mixture over the chicken.
Layer remaining chicken onto mixture and top with remaining lemon and garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Baste occasionally.

title: cheese 'n' chicken dinner
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a sack.
Shake to blend ingredients.
Add 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time and shake to coat the chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, in butter.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 15 minutes more or until golden brown.
Mix together soup and milk; heat in pan and pour over chicken.
Move pieces toward center of pan.
Arrange biscuits around meat and bake 10 minutes more.
Top each biscuit with a quarter slice of cheese. Put remaining cheese on chicken and bake 5 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: french onion beef stew
directions: Note:
The vegetables are cut in large pieces so they won't overcook while the beef cubes are stewing to tenderness.
Quick cooking tapioca, added at the beginning, disappears, yet thickens the liquid to a transparent gravy while the stew is cooking.

title: punch
directions: Chill all juices, ginger ale and sugar.
Pour in punch bowl and add sherbet when ready to serve.

title: holiday sausage rolls
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine with chives and cream cheese in bowl; mix well.
Unroll one can dough on floured surface; press to seal perforations.
Spread with half the sausage mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll, from long side repeat with remaining dough and filling.
Freeze for 20 minutes or until firm.
Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Cut rolls into 1/4 in slices.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
May freeze baked slices for up to 2 weeks and reheat at 400 degrees for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: caramel brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco until very light.
Add brown sugar and cream well.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Being and end with dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, milk and pepper.
Shape into meatballs and fry in small amount of fat until browned.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs. Cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until sauce begins to thicken. Serve over rice.

title: angel custard
directions: Pinch off pieces of cake and spread in bottom of large bowl. Cover with layer of pudding, followed by a layer of pie filling, coconut and Dream Whip.
Repeat.
Top with Dream Whip, coconut and cherries.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown
onions
lightly in vegetable oil.
Add hamburger and cook until brown.
Add catsup, salt, mustard, vinegar and beans. Let
all get hot.
Put in baking dish or pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: southwestern chicken salad spirals
directions: Drain roasted red bell peppers well, pressing with paper towel; chop.
Stir together peppers, chicken, and next seven ingredients.
Cover and chill for at least two hours.
Spoon evenly over tortillas and roll up.
Cut each roll into five slices, securing with toothpicks.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Do not drain pineapple.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add 3 eggs.
Mix well.
Add almond, lemon and vanilla and mix.
Add sour milk, flour, salt and baking soda to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough on floured surface and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: raisin buddy banana mini muffins
directions: Spray muffin pans or loaf pan with cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put bananas into blender and blend until smooth. Combine in a bowl with eggs and oil.
In another bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add banana mixture until moistened.
Stir in raisins.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix
altogether.
Bake in an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish for about 35 to 60 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: cherry-pineapple upside-down cake(makes one 9-inch cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat together 1/4 cup of the butter and the granulated sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Melt the remaining 1/4 cup of butter in 9-inch ovenproof skillet or 9-inch cake pan.
Stir in brown sugar; spread to cover bottom of pan.
Cover with pineapple. Reserve a few cherries for garnish, if desired.
Spoon remaining cherries over pineapple; top with batter.
Bake for 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and turn upside down onto cake plate.
Garnish with reserved cherries and mint, if desired.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook vegetables.
Put through tomato strainer.
Put back on stove.
Bring to boil.
Add salt, sugar and butter; add water to cornstarch to make paste.
When this comes to rolling boil, seal in pint or quart jars.

title: cheese mold
directions: Mix together except pecans and preserves.
Mix with your hands.
After mixed good, sprinkle 1/4 cup chopped pecans in mold. Spray mold with Pam.
Press cheese mixture into mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans. Put preserves in center of mold.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together first
5 ingredients and cook until thick.
Add a lump of butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites on high; add 4 tablespoons of sugar.
Spread on pie.

title: sponge cakes with lemon filling
directions: Separate eggs, beating egg yolks until lemon colored. Add sugar to egg yolks. Beat until light and creamy. Add the juice and grated rind of lemon. Stir in the flour. Finally fold in the egg whites, beaten to a stiff froth.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes. Into sides of cake, make a slit and fill with lemon filling.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Combine oranges, apples and bananas.
Serve with Salad Dressing.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Place remaining ingredients and 1 cup of sauce in a large bowl.
Blend.
Place meat mixture in a 2-quart Pyrex loaf pan.
Pour on remaining sauce.
Run knife along outside edge of pan to allow sauce to seep down side of meat loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: funche de maiz
directions: Tortillas as "bread":
Corn or flour tortillas may be used.

title: woman's wonderful potato bake
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 12 pan.
Mix together melted butter, soup, cheese, onion and sour cream, pour over potatoes. Top with crushed cornflakes.
Pour another stick of butter (melted) over the top and bake uncovered at 350° for 45-50 minutes.
Freezes well before baking.

title: wiener appetizer
directions: Combine barbecue sauce and pepper jelly.
Heat, then cut wieners into bite size and heat in sauce for a few minutes. Serve hot from chafing dish or buffet server.

title: chicken salad
directions: Grind chicken in food grinder.
Chop egg whites very fine. Mix with chicken.
Make a paste with the egg yellows, 1/2 teaspoon each of mustard, black pepper, salt, a sufficient amount of vinegar to make it palatable and also 1 tablespoon oil.
Add to chicken with chopped celery according to taste.
Will keep for a good week.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn temperature back to 300° and bake about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cake is supposed to fall.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in tube pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: greek and spinach quiche
directions: In a 9-inch quiche dish, prick pastry bottom and sides with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and prick with fork.
Bake 5 minutes.
Cook spinach and drain.
Combine spinach and remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef.
After browning, drain meat.
Add chili beans, chopped onion and diced green pepper.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
(If you like it more on the soupy side, leave kettle covered.
For a more meatier meal, leave uncovered to let steam and moisture escape.)

title: extra chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan. Stir all of the ingredients together until thick.
Spread evenly in the greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Melt water and sugar in a frying pan on medium heat.
Add peanuts.
Stir constantly (over medium heat) until all liquid is absorbed and nuts are coated.
Pour onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Pick apart with fork; stirring every 10 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup, milk, 1/2 can onion rings and pepper. Mix well and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake for 5 minutes more.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together and refrigerate.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix pecans, cake mix and margarine together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients (cream cheese, sugar and eggs) and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put together in a large bowl the flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Make a hole or well in the center.
Add Wesson oil, pecans, eggs, apples and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: cloud nine salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and add the juice to the cream cheese and sugar and mix, then beat with a spoon.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: kid's kool-aid punch
directions: Mix in large gallon jar.
This makes 1 1/2 gallons.
Kids love it at school parties!

title: fresh pear bread
directions: Pare, halve and core pears; chop to make 1 cup.
In a large bowl, beat oil and sugar until blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to oil-sugar mixture and continue to beat until well blended.
Add nuts and pears; mix well.
Spoon into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out and cool on rack.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: Bring the water to a boil; add the walnuts.
Return to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Drain.
Dump into large bowl with the sugar; stir to coat well.
Heat 1 inch of oil to 350°.
Fry half of the nuts at a time until golden brown.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Drain on a foil-covered cookie sheet.
(Don't use paper towels.)

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel carrots, chop or grate. Add remaining ingredients. Blend in enough mayonnaise to blend.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: De-stem mushrooms and wash thoroughly.
Cook bacon.
Combine bacon and cream cheese.
Stuff mushrooms with the combined cream cheese and bacon.
Place on buttered baking pan and cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Use 2 tablespoons butter instead of salt pork if more convenient.
Dice and put in a deep pan.
Cook slowly until fat is melted and pork bits are crisp and brown.
Add onion; cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add potatoes and 2 cups water, cooking until potatoes are tender.
Add the cream-style corn, 2 cups milk and the Carnation milk.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sinful salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour melted butter.
Grease sides also.
Now add rest of ingredients, one by one, on top of the other.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: whole wheat buttermilk banana pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and add to dry.
Don't overmix.

title: avocado salad
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add minced onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise and salt.
Serve on tomato slices and garnish with Doritos.

title: reese cups
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Chill until chocolate hardens.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix crackers and cheese in bowl.
Beat eggs and add juice from asparagus.
In large square baking dish, pour a little of the juice-egg mixture to cover bottom.
Add a thin layer of cheese cracker mixture.
Layer remaining ingredients as follows:
1 can asparagus, 1/2 can mushroom soup and a layer of cracker/cheese mixture (spoon some of the juice-egg mixture over this).
Repeat, ending with remaining juice-egg mixture.
Dot with butter and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Half and debone chicken breasts.
Combine next 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Cover chicken with mixture and let stand overnight.
Remove chicken from mixture and roll in bread crumbs. Melt butter and shortening.
Put half over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Add remaining butter and cook additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large pot, saute chopped sausage and chicken in a little oil or butter until done. Chop vegetables and add.
Cook until soft.
Add spices and 3 cups of water, turn up the heat and bring to a boil.
Add tomato paste and rice.
Stir well.
Add peeled shrimp.
Cover the pot and turn the heat down to low. Cook for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Converted rice is especially good in this recipe.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix juices and let stand an hour.
Pour in ginger ale and serve over ice.
This is a delicious drink in hot summer.

title: asparagus and parmesan salad
directions: Place asparagus in a steamer basket.
Place basket in a large skillet over boiling water.
Reduce heat, cover and steam for 5 to 7 minutes or until asparagus is crisp tender.
Remove from steamer and cool slightly.
Meanwhile, for dressing, in a screw top jar, combine olive oil, lemon juice, thyme, mustard, garlic, salt, and pepper to taste.
Cover and shake until combined.
Arrange asparagus on a platter.
Drizzle with dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese, parsley and if desired basil/garlic.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Put the diced rhubarb in an unbaked pie shell. Mix together sugar, flour and beaten eggs.
Pour over diced rhubarb.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top. Bake at 325° to 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over first 3 ingredients to melt.
Dissolve yeast in cold water; add beaten eggs.
Add flour.
Place in refrigerator.
When ready to use, take out and shape into rolls. Let stand to raise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed onions florentine
directions: Peel onions; cut 1/2-inch slice off sprout end and just enough off the root end to allow onion to sit flat.
In shallow baking dish, arrange onions, add water and cook on High, covered, for 11 to 13 minutes or until partially cooked.
Carefully remove centers of onion as they pop up, leaving 1/4 to 1/2-inch shell.
Chop enough onion centers to make 1/4 cup. (Freeze remaining onion centers for later use.)

title: creamy pecan pralines
directions: Caramelize half cup of sugar (melted over low flame, stirring constantly).
Add 1/3 stick butter to melted sugar.
Bring to a boil sugar, corn syrup and cream.
Add caramelized mixture and cook to soft ball stage.
Add rest of butter, pecans and vanilla. Stir well until begins to thicken.
Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls to cool.

title: fresh fruit jams
directions: Mix first three ingredients in large pot.
Cook 45 minutes, boiling.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Put into hot jars. Seal with hot lids.
Makes 5 pints.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Remove crust from bread and lightly spread with butter.
Line casserole dish with bread. Cook and drain sausage; spoon sausage over bread and sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix egg, milk and salt.
Pour over cheese. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove 15 minutes before cooking.
Cook for 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: island broiled chicken
directions: Combine salad oil, lemon juice, soy sauce, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper for marinating sauce. Seal chicken and sauce in plastic bag. Marinate in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours, turning several times. Place in broiler pan without rack. Broil 5 to 7-inches from heat about 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Baste occasionally with sauce. Turn; broil 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salmon log
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill.
Roll into log and cover with 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons chopped parsley.

title: sauerkraut and tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered, or until meat is done at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: collards
directions: Let meat boil until tender.
Add collards to this meat and broth.
After collards have boiled and gone down, put lard, if you like, sugar and salt.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl; add next 5 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with mixer 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour batter into a 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; drizzle with Lemon Glaze and cool completely.

title: bev's famous cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften. Mix all ingredients except pecans. Form into 1-inch patty or ball. Cover outside with chopped nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed zucchini with black bean sauce
directions: Mix well and place approximately 1 heaping teaspoon in each zucchini shell.
Steam for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook or zucchini will not hold its shape.
Serve with black bean sauce.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion, celery and peppers.
Mix all and top with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Mix flour, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Stir in cream, chopped dates, raisins and pecans.
Fill the shell.
Bake the pie until set, about 30 minutes.
When cool, top with meringue and finish baking.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Add remaining flour and beat until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before baking, cut off amount needed and return rest to refrigerator.

title: quick chili-rice dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; add spices, corn, pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box; chill until soft set.
Mix pineapple, sugar and nuts; chill.
When jello is ready, mix with one container of Cool Whip and pineapple mixture.
Add strawberries and mix well.
Tear cakes in small chunks and layer alternately with mixture until cakes are used up, ending with mixture on top.
Put remaining container of Cool Whip on top and garnish with coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: "any idiot" lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell.
Refrigerate.
If you want the pie a little darker in color, add a few drops of food coloring.

title: crowd pleaser
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 pan.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown beef and onion.
Drain fat from meat.
Season meat with garlic powder and cracked pepper. Add tomato sauce to beef mixture and stir well.

title: grandmother's coconut pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: Melt butter.
Add cheese which has been cut into small pieces. Cook over hot water, stirring until cheese melts.
Add salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour in milk, slowly.
Add beaten eggs until mixture gets thick.
Serve over toast.

title: "stuff"
directions: In a large frypan, brown ground beef; drain. Stir in seasoning mix and add tomato sauce; simmer, while preparing crust. Separate one can biscuit dough into 10 biscuits. Pull apart each into two layers. Arrange over bottom of ungreased 13 x 19-inch pan. Spoon hot mixture over crust. Arrange cheese slices on top of this mixture. Separate second can of biscuit dough into 10 biscuits. Pull apart each into 2 layers and arrange on top of cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup, milk, soy sauce and dash of pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir top with remaining onions.
Bake for 5 minutes more.
Serves about 4 cups.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Bring to a boil.
Immediately pour hot dressing over cabbage mixture.
Allow to cool and blend thoroughly.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Stays crisp and fresh for 9 days.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs together beating until light and fluffy.
Add milk.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into crust.
Chill and enjoy.

title: elegant champagne punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except champagne and let stand in refrigerator until pineapple is thawed.
Just before serving, add well-chilled champagne.
Mix lightly and serve immediately.
Makes about 15 servings.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients to make sauce.
Add cheese and cook until thickened.
Layer ham and potatoes and top with sauce.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: cheri's smoked rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lima beans and sausage bake
directions: Fry sausage 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into pieces and arrange in buttered casserole alternately with cooked beans.
Blend in saucepan over low heat margarine, milk and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over beans and sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: diced apple cake
directions: Mix as usual.
Mix oil, apples and sugar until mixed well. Add soda and raisins or walnuts.

title: stuffed date cookies
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, egg and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix. Dip stuffed dates (with pecans) into batter.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost with brown butter and powdered sugar.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar to boiling (2-3 minutes in the microwave).
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Add cereal, stir until well coated.	Press into 9 x 13 greased pan.	Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together, stir until mixed and smooth. (Approximately 3 minutes in microwave, stir halfway.)
Spread over top.

title: chicken with beef and bacon
directions: *Use Buddig thin sliced sandwich beef.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popped corn warm in oven.
Mix sugar and cream of tartar in 2-quart saucepan.
Add and mix until dissolved Karo, water, vinegar and chocolate if desired.
Bring to boil and boil without stirring until reaching hard ball stage (drop of mixture makes hard ball that remains solid when picked up with fingers when a drop is placed in cup of cold water).
Remove from heat and get popcorn out of oven.
Stir in soda.
Mixture will foam.
Add vanilla if chocolate omitted.
Pour over hot popcorn and mix thoroughly with greased wooden spoons.
Grease fingers and pat lightly into balls when thoroughly mixed.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand 1/2 hour.
Cream margarine.
Add salt, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with oatmeal mixture. Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: curried apricot pork chops
directions: Dip chops in egg; dredge in breadcrumbs. Brown in hot oil; place in shallow 2 qt. baking dish. Drain apricots, reserving juice. Combine juice, brown sugar and curry; pour over chops. Place apricots around chops. Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until tender. Serves 4.

title: grilled pepper chicken breast
directions: Cream butter in food processor.
Mix spices; add to butter. Add jalapenos.
Process until thoroughly mixed.
Gently lift chicken skin and spread butter mixture between meat and skin. Spread over outer skin.

title: caramel cake filling
directions: Put 1 cup sugar with 2 tablespoons butter into a heavy skillet. Cook over a slow fire stirring slowly until sugar is dissolved and becomes a syrup.
Into another boiler, break 1 egg yolk and beat, then add 1 cup of milk and set over low flame to heat (don't boil or it will curdle).
Add this to sugar syrup and cook until all lumps are dissolved.
Mix some flour and water together to make a thin paste and, if caramel is not thick enough to spread, add some a little at a time until it is the desired thickness.
Add vanilla and spread on cake.

title: shrimp spread
directions: With electric mixer, cream the cream cheese, butter, lemon, salt and pepper.
Let shrimp stand in cold water for 30 minutes. Drain.
Mix together.
Spread on crackers.

title: meat balls for soup
directions: Let meat go through meat chopper 4 to 6 times or more.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly.
Add egg and milk slowly, mixing constantly.
Form into small balls and drop into boiling water.
Cook 5 minutes.
Rinse with cold water in a strainer.
Do not cook too many meat balls at a time, about 10 to 12, depending on the size of pot.
(Can use dumpling for soup recipe with this.)

title: strawberries
directions: You will also need artificial green plastic hulls (purchased at candy stores, 50 for about $1.25).

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in hot shortening in skillet.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and butter.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan, sprinkle nuts and coconut over the bottom of the pan.
Pour cake mix on top of the coconut and pecans.
Then spoon cream cheese mixture over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve!

title: fat-free fajitas
directions: Chop peppers.
Slice onions.
Spray nonstick pan with cooking spray.
Saute peppers and onions.
(For soft vegetables place in microwave bowl.
Cover with Saran Wrap and cook for 5 to 7 minutes.)
Cut chicken or turkey in small pieces.
Saute meat and seafood.
Add vegetables, cilantro and black pepper.
Stir to combine.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until done, bone and put in broth; keep hot. Cook carrots, celery, peas and onion in small amount of water until tender.
Combine with chicken and put in casserole, place biscuits on chicken and vegetables and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: brussels sprouts marinade
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts until tender; drain and cool.
Combine Brussels sprouts, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Pour dressing over top and mix.
Best if refrigerated 2 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: souper chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: fruit logs
directions: Crush wafers and mix all ingredients together (except confectioners sugar),
by hand, and roll into 4 logs.
Roll into confectioners sugar. Put in foil and freeze or refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Allow to cool.
Make pudding as directed.
Cut cake in half, making 2 separate cakes.
Add pudding evenly on both cakes.
Drain pineapple; add 1 can to each cake evenly.
Top with cherries.
Add sliced bananas.
Spread Cool Whip evenly.
Top with swirls of Hershey chocolate and walnuts.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add egg yolks and stir.
Add cooking oil in egg mixture; beat well.
Pour egg mixture over apples.
Then add dry ingredients.
Stir with spoon; pour in greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes or longer.

title: pecan pie supreme
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in corn syrup, butter, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.
Center should be slightly less set than edges when done.

title: tops-style chili
directions: Cook ground turkey, add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings.

title: black corsicana cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add coffee, vanilla, flour, cocoa and salt.
Blend.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk and add to mixture.
Divide between three 8-inch cake pans (greased and floured or use Pam).
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with Nancy's Chocolate Icing.

title: blueberry cream dessert
directions: Mix sugar and gelatin; add water.
Heat and stir until dissolved (microwave approximately 4 minutes on High).
Blend yogurt into gelatin mixture.
Add vanilla.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in Cool Whip and stir in blueberries.
Chill until set.

title: baked beans special
directions: Cook celery, onion and green peppers in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings until soft but not brown.
Combine all other ingredients except bacon.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place bacon strips on top and bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix together the strawberry jello, boiling and cold water.
Let chill.
Then add cold cooked rice and milk.
Mix into the rice. Then add crushed pineapple and juice and chopped nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: pickles in a hurry
directions: Combine sliced cucumbers with skin, chopped peppers and onion. Sprinkle with salt and celery seed.
Stir gently.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: mom's toffee bars
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Spread onto greased jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven off.
Remove pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Return to oven for 1 to 3 minutes.
Spread chocolate to frost.
Cool, cut and enjoy!

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in the cold water; add to soup, stirring well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into an oiled (I use Pam) four-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.
(I use Harris Select crabmeat and Campbell's 1/3 less salt soup.)

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well and stir in pecans.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets before removing.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: In small saucepan, heat corn (whole kernel) with liquid to boiling point.
Add rest of ingredients to just reach boiling. Serve with oyster crackers.

title: quick spaghetti with smoked salmon for 2
directions: Microwave setting High.
Place half of butter in 12-cup (3 liter) casserole.
Add vegetables and season.
Cover and microwave 3 minutes.
Stir in hot spaghetti, smoked salmon, remaining butter and parsley; let stand 1 minute.
Top with grated cheese and serve.

title: make-a-meal soup
directions: Brown onion in oil in large pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer thirty minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy cheese balls
directions: Place Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt in food processor or grate cheeses together and combine with Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Then mix in pecans. Roll mixture into 2 large balls.
Combine chili powder, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Roll balls into spice mixture.
Balls can be frozen.

title: reuben spread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat in saucepan.
Great for dip or spread.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook together and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made from the egg whites.
Brown in oven.

title: grilled ranch steak
directions: Dissolve salad dressing mix in water and olive oil.
Grill flank steak for 4 minutes.
Brush top with half of mixture. Grill 3 minutes longer.
Turn and grill 4 minutes.
Brush on remaining mixture.
Grill 3 to 5 minutes more.
Slice diagonally. Serves 4.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients except strawberries and nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in strawberries and nuts. Pour into 2 greased or 5 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Adjust time if you use small pans.

title: sausage and baked beans
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add onion, beans and sugar.
In a small bowl, dissolve ginger, dry mustard and salt in the hot water.
Stir into bean mixture.
Pour into 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix well with other ingredients.
Mold in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight and then roll in chopped nuts.

title: ham rice pinwheels
directions: In a medium bowl, cream cheese until fluffy.
Add rice, olives, onion, horseradish, pickle relish and Worcestershire sauce; blend well.

title: sonya's cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix sugar and pineapple together and cook 20 minutes.
Poke holes on top of cake and pour pineapple mixture all over cake.
Let cool completely. Make up pudding by using 3 cups of milk.
Pour on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
Add 3/4 cup of coconut on top of Cool Whip.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients. Spread topping on chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: white chocolate peanut butter crunch
directions: In a large glass bowl, microwave coating on high for 2 minutes or until melted, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth; then add marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon full onto wax paper.
Let stand for 15 minutes or until firm.

title: sugar-free pineapple supreme
directions: Cream the cheese, add milk slowly, and add the instant pudding.
Mix for about 1 minute.
Add pineapple and stir.
Pour into a pie plate with or without a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and water with mixer until creamy.
Stir in with a spoon the flour.
You may add 1/4 cup more, if needed.
Also add baking soda, salt and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 14 to 16 minutes or until cookies are very lightly golden brown.

title: hamburger bean pot soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put meat and the remaining ingredients into a large pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and set aside.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine noodles and chicken (deboned and cut into small pieces) in a glass casserole pan
Add cream of chicken soup, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Mix thoroughly.
Add small amount of cheeses to top and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash with onion (as much onion as you like).
Mix together with the rest of ingredients and put in greased casserole dish and bake 400° for 30 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown meats together in skillet, starting with sausage.
Add garlic, black pepper and poultry seasoning.
Remove from skillet, leaving grease.
Add diced pepper and onion.
Cook until it starts getting tender.
Add Creole seasoning and poultry seasoning and stir in hot sauce to taste.
Remove from heat and stir in uncooked rice, coating with grease mixture.

title: bubbling cheese bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Spread cheese mixture on cut side of each bread half.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 3 minutes or until bubbly or lightly browned.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Makes about 28 appetizers.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, cream brown sugar and margarine. Slowly add dry mixture, blending well.
Add apple, egg and vanilla. Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and enjoy!
Makes 24 cookies.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut lengthwise and place in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drain apricots, reserving liquid.
Add water, if necessary, to make 1 cup liquid.
Arrange apricots over potatoes.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and grated orange peel. Cook until thick.
Sprinkle raisins over potatoes and apricots and pour liquid all over.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In a microwave safe bowl, combine milk & chocolate chips. Microwave, uncovered, on high on 1-2 minutes or until chips are melted; stir until smooth.
Stir in cracker crumbs, walnuts & vanilla.
Shape into a 17 in. log; roll in sugar.
Wrap in plastic. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm.
Unwrap and cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Yields:
5 1/2 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in blender and blend.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Combine mixture and add flour in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake 60 to 70 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat together butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet.
Press down center of each ball and place a cherry in each.

title: mozzarella dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 4 to 6 hours for flavor to blend.

title: lasagna supreme
directions: Brown chuck and pour off excess fat.
Place tomato juice and all seasoning in a slow cooker for 3 to 4 hours. Add meat and let simmer for rest of day, adding juice and skimming grease as needed.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and corn meal.
Add eggs, melted butter, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Beat until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is golden.

title: pasta e fagioli soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions; drain.
Add all other ingredients except beans and pasta.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook pasta for 5 minutes; drain.
Add beans and cooked pasta to soup.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Extra water may be added for thinner consistency.

title: apple roll
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add vanilla or lemon.
Bake in hot oven for 20 minutes.

title: ham and pecan stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Cut ham into bite size strips.
Cut green pepper into 1-inch pieces.
Stir pineapple juice, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and red pepper.
Over high heat, add 1 tablespoon oil, add pecans and stir-fry until toasted, about 30 seconds; remove.
Add green pepper, 1 minute.
Remove and add remaining oil; add ham and stir-fry 2 minutes. Push ham to side; add cornstarch mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add pepper, pineapple and pecans; cook 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: janean's clam chowder
directions: In saucepan add clam juice and enough water to cook potatoes in.
Cook until tender.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
In the fat, fry onions.
Set aside and fry mushrooms.
Add all ingredients together except clams and bring just to boil, then add a flour thickener (flour and water).
Now add clams and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook clams.
Also be sure to stir often so as not to burn.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate fudge sundae cake
directions: Spray with Pam and mix in 9 x 9-inch or medium glass baking bowl the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in until smooth the milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and spread evenly, then sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over all.
Do not stir.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve over ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: amaretto-pecan cornmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Generously grease and flour 10-inch fluted tube pan with a small amount of shortening.
Beat together margarine and sugars in large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream and Amaretto.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to margarine mixture, mixing until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared pan, spreading evenly to edges.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean (surface will appear slightly wet in center).
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove to rack to cool completely.
Prepare Amaretto glaze.
Drizzle over cake.
Garnish, if desired.
Store tightly covered.

title: fat-free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, Karo and vanilla until well mixed.
Add raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven 10 minutes or until firm.
Do not overbake.

title: berry barbecued pork roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper. Place roast fat side up on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Bake potatoes. Peel and sweeten to taste. Add margarine and mix well. Place 1 or 2 marshmallows in potato ball. Work potatoes around marshmallows. Roll in corn flakes. Place in greased pan and heat on low until marshmallows begin to melt. Serve hot.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into golf ball sized meatballs.
Mixture is moist and handles better if very cold. Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Allow fat to drain off while cooling.
Makes 35 to 40 meat balls.

title: easy pork chop bake
directions: Add to pan and cook until mixture thickens.
Serve over hot rice.

title: lye soap
directions: Dissolve lye in cold water (use iron, enamel or stainless steel pot, never aluminum).
Allow to cool.
Dissolve or melt lard and remove from heat.
Pour lukewarm lye solution in lukewarm grease, stirring to mix thoroughly.
As it cools, add perfume if desired and beat until mixture becomes white and fluffy.
Pour into molds to set.
When firm, cut into cakes and separate.
Allow to harden and air dry
at least 2 weeks before using.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Mix, cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: calico potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, whole with skins on.
(Should be 6 cups diced, cooked potatoes, about 6 medium potatoes.)
Skin and dice while warm.
Immediately add the vinegar, prepared mustard, pepper, celery seed and salt, then add the cucumber, onion, green pepper, pimento and eggs.
Mix Cool Whip and mayonnaise together and add to potato mixture.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: diet tennessee apple pie
directions: You will also need a 9-inch pie pan.

title: carrot and pepper soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium high heat.
Add onion and cumin seed.
Cook, stirring often, until onion is soft, about 10 minutes.
Add sweet potato, carrots, bell pepper, hot pepper and 3 1/2 cups broth.
Cover and heat to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with Pepperidge Farm corn bread stuffing. Mix other ingredients; pour into casserole.
Top lightly with stuffing and 1 small chopped onion.
Heat at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: homestyle beans and biscuits casserole
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese and biscuits; blend well.
Evenly spread bean mixture in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over beans and top with biscuits.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until beans are heated through and biscuits are golden brown.

title: meatballs
directions: In a 10-inch skillet (nonstick), brown onion and garlic in oil over moderately high heat for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Combine bread and mix with water in a large bowl.
Add beef, onion and garlic (don't wash skillet), parsley, salt, pepper, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in eggs and mix with a wooden spoon until well blended.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown on all sides in skillet onion was cooked in, about 15 minutes.
Then place in spaghetti sauce and simmer.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese during the last 15 minutes of baking time.
The meat of a whole, cooked chicken may be used.
A very good recipe.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water, syrup and peanuts and cook until light brown or to thread.
Remove from burner and add salt, butter and vanilla, then soda last.

title: aunt mary's pecan pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: nut mix
directions: Saute bread cubes in 4 tablespoons of the margarine until golden brown.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of sugar; mix well.
In a large (covered) bowl, combine the bread cubes, walnuts, apricots, almonds and apples.
In a small saucepan combine remaining margarine, remaining sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Heat until the sauce is smooth.
Pour over mixture; coat evenly.
Store tightly in a covered bowl in the refrigerator.
Enjoy!!

title: broccoli lima bake
directions: Cook vegetables, barely tender.
Blend soup, sour cream and onion; stir into cooked vegetables.
Add chestnuts.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with Rice Krispies that have been lightly browned in oleo.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted
water and drain.
Combine with ingredients, save 1/2 cup
cheese
and cracker crumbs to go on top.
Put in large	greased baking dish.
Add extra cheese and crackers on top and cook at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Peel and core apples.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch.
Cut into 6 squares.
Place 1 apple on each square. Sprinkle apples with cinnamon.
Place butter and brown sugar into centers of pastry dough to overlap on top of apples.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat water, sugar and vanilla to rolling boil.
Pour over apple dumplings.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.
Serves 6.

title: chicken in a biscuit
directions: Combine soft cream cheese, chicken, onion, salt and pepper. Separate dinner rolls into rectangles, firmly pressing perforations and seal.
Cut each rectangle into 4 (4 x 5-inch) rectangles.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of chicken mixture on each rectangle.
Fold sides and ends of dough toward center and seal.
Shape into biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Cut dried beef into very tiny pieces, chop the onions including the tops.
Mix all ingredients together, chill overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the last 3 ingredients.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Let set for at least 3 hours.
Serve cold.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine together and put in a shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This can be put together several hours ahead or even overnight.

title: fried chicken grandma's way
directions: Before you start to fry chicken, let it soak all night in a large bowl with salt and water.
Remove chicken from refrigerator. Drain water and pepper lightly.
You may also use garlic powder if you desire to.
Flour chicken, then place in skillet of Wesson oil. Cover with lid.
Cook on medium-high until golden brown.

title: touchdown chocolate bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add egg. Mix until well blended.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumb mixture. Press remainder evenly into baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
In saucepan, combine condensed milk and 1 cup of chips.
Melt over low heat until smooth.
Spread evenly into prepared crust.
Add nuts and remaining chips.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store at room temperature.

title: grits souffle
directions: Cook grits in salted water 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving a small amount of the butter.
Put in long baking dish and brush top with remaining butter.
Cook at 300 degrees for 1 hour.

title: tangy chip dip
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature and mix well.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar. Pat into lightly greased 13 x 9 bake pan. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 12- 15 minutes, till golden.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with 1 package of Ritz crackers (crumbled) and 1 stick melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and almond extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each at low speed just until blended.
Pour into an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.

title: marinated 2-bean salad
directions: Cut pepper in thin strips. Cut onion in small rings. Drain beans.
In a large bowl, combine drained beans and vegetables.
In small bowl, whisk together remaining ingredients and pour over bean mixture.
Add additional balsamic vinegar to taste, if desired.
Refrigerate at least several hours or overnight.

title: "peanut butter sheet cake"
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, water and peanut butter.
Remove from heat and add flour, granulated sugar and salt.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and soda.
Pour on greased and floured cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Make icing while cake is baking.

title: grandy cake
directions: Use a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, soda, salt, eggs and crushed pineapple.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle nuts and brown sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, butter, evaporated milk and vanilla in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Pour over cake after cooked, yet still hot from the oven.

title: salmon banquet pie(served with tartar sauce)
directions: Combine eggs, milk, butter, onion, parsley & seasonings. Break salmon into chunks, removing bones & skin. Stir salmon into egg mixture. Pour into a well greased 8 inch pie plate. Prepare your own pie crust & roll 1/8 inch thick, cut an 8 inch circle, then cut circle into 6 wedges. Arrange on top of pie. Bake in a 425° oven for 25 minutes. Serve immediately. You may serve tartar sauce on top of hot wedges.

title: jacquie's mexican dip
directions: Mix altogether and microwave for 8 minutes.

title: 5 minute frosting
directions: Beat egg whites, but not stiff.
Heat syrup (do not boil). Pour into beaten egg whites slowly while beating.
Beat 5 minutes. Frosting is very good on coconut cake, pies and ice cream.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut each biscuit into fourths and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with nuts as you add biscuits.
Combine brown sugar and margarine; heat until melted and sugar is dissolved. Pour over biscuits.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly and turn onto plate, then cut.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in large non metallic bowl.
Cover with equal parts vinegar and water to which the spices have been added. Cover and refrigerate for 4 days to a week.
Turn meat daily. Cook at a simmer until done in the marinade, adding a little more of the liquids if need during cooking.
Remove meat and keep warm. Strain liquid to remove spices and return to pan and heat.
Crush gingersnaps to fine crumbs using a rolling pin, and add the liquid to thicken to gravy.
Use as many as necessary.

title: south seas chicken and bananas
directions: In a food processor or blender, blend the lemon juice, condensed milk, milk, coconut and cardamom until smooth.
Pour into a bowl. Dip bananas into milk mixture.
Roll in cornflakes and set aside.
Dip chicken into remaining milk mixture.
Roll in the remaining cornflakes and place in two greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup of the melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Arrange bananas over the chicken. Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until chicken juices run clear.
Garnish with kiwi and starfruit, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes in food processor or blender.
Add eggs, flour, onion and seasonings.
Blend.
Pan-fry to golden brown.
Serve with applesauce.

title: cheese cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 275° for 35 to 40 minutes in medium size skillet.
Goes best with homemade chili, spaghetti, or baked potato soup.

title: smothered lettuce
directions: Chop lettuce and onions.
Add seasonings to taste.
Pour vinegar over all.
Cut bacon in strips; fry until crisp.
Put on lettuce and pour hot drippings over all.
Toss and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp and spinach quiche
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pie crust and bake for 5 minutes at 375°.
Line bottom of crust with thin layer of Swiss cheese, then sprinkle on Colby and Cheddar cheeses and top with remaining Swiss cheese.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg and spinach.
Pour mixture on top of cheeses.
Sprinkle scallions on top; dot with melted butter.
Place pie on nonstick cookie sheet and bake at 375° for an hour or until mixture is set.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: million dollar pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Empty milk into large bowl and stir in lemon juice; add fruits and Cool Whip.
Stir well and put into crusts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: snowball cake
directions: Remove all the brown from the angel food cake and pinch into bite-sized pieces.
Set aside.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup.
Add milk to make 3/4 cup.
Flake salmon, removing bones and skin.
Blend in egg.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Spoon into greased pan or 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: java brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Microwave the butter, cocoa powder and coffee until the butter is melted. Whisk in sugar, eggs, and vanilla. Add in the flour and nuts. Spread into greased pan. Bake for approx. 30 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt butter; stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix together (do not beat).
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put in cold oven and set at 250°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until it cracks slightly.
Cut in squares.

title: strawberry dream dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While warm, flatten cake as much as possible.
Cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake.
Mix 1 cup boiling water with jello.
Add frozen strawberries.
Let thicken slightly and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mama's cornbread casserole
directions: Heat beans and pour over crumbled cornbread.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix tomatoes, onion, bell pepper, mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Pour over pintos.
Heat about 15 minutes in 300 degree oven. Crumble cooked bacon on top before serving.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a glass bowl.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Place butter in a small bowl with electric mixer; beat several minutes until creamy.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla, then milk, a little at a time, and beat well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat with electric mixer.
Bake in oblong cake pan at 325° for 1 hour.
If frosting is desired, frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix well.
Fold in a large container.
Use as salad or dessert.
Can be frozen.
Refrigerate for a day, then dip it out in serving size scoops and freeze.
Take it out of the freezer; let it thaw about 1 hour.

title: antipasto
directions: Mix the first 12 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients to taste.
Store in refrigerator until time to serve.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: diet cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and mix.
Add unbeaten eggs and mix.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Six calories each.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add all other ingredients except macaroni, beans and cabbage.
Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Add last 3 ingredients and simmer until they are tender.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add jello and red food coloring. Allow mixture to cool, then add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip before serving.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Start to boil water with hamburger, onions, celery and bouillon cubes.
When it has boiled for 20 minutes, add orzo. When it boils again, lower the flame and add other vegetables. Simmer slowly 3/4 of an hour more.

title: scottish beef and potato pie(shepherd's pie)
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into 3/8-inch thick slices.
Place slices into pan with cold water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring water to the boil and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender, but not falling apart.
Drain and set aside.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except rhubarb.
Mix a little flour in rhubarb, then fold in cake batter.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch loaf or oblong pan; sprinkle top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon, mixed together.
Nuts are optional.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, until done.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with meat balls, sausage, sliced ham or as a spread over cream cheese with crackers.

title: aunt penny's ham casserole
directions: Mix sop and milk in buttered casserole.
Add ham, cheese, elbow spaghetti, mushrooms and horseradish.
Top casserole with cracker crumbs which have been tossed in butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine dry ingredients in tall saucepan.
Stir in milk and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until a soft ball stage.
This is when a small amount dropped into a cup of cold water forms a ball.
Set aside.
Combine butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Quickly add before it sets.
Cool to room temperature.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until combined. Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan to a wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white to peak.
Add sugar and vanilla slowly.
Dip nuts in above mixture individually.
Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes, turn oven off, leave for at least 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet at 350°.
Mix in sugar, peanuts, and syrup.
Cook at 350° for about 10 or 15 minutes or until golden tan.
Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda.
While mixture is still hot.
The mixture will foam, so stir good.
Pour mixture on tinfoil lined cookie sheet and spread quickly.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yield: 15 - 20 servings.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crackers and 1/4 cup butter.
Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie plate.
Cook onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, but not brown.
Put on top of cracker crumbs.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
I use casserole.

title: chocolate chip cookies(mmmm!)
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels.

title: korean salad
directions: Mix the dressing and onion and add to the chopped up spinach in a bowl.
Add water chestnuts and also add bean sprouts.
Then crumble cooked bacon on
top.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: stellas - crescent pastry cookies
directions: Combine pecans, sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside. Sift flour into medium sized bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in sour cream until dough holds together.
Divide into 4 balls, wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 6 hours. Sprinkle work surface with flour, then heavily with sugar.
Roll one dough ball into a 10-inch round; divide into 8 or 12 wedges (depending on size crescent you want).
Brush circle with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of the nut/sugar mixture.
Roll into crescent, starting from the wide end, tucking the point underneath.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with egg white.
Repeat with each dough ball.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.
Remove crescents to cooling rack; drizzle with confectioners icing.

title: sweet and sour cabbage and beans
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients except beans. Bring cabbage mixture to a boil while stirring. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans to cabbage and cook 5 minutes to heat through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Stir in yogurt.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Sift flour, measure 4 cups, then sift again with baking soda and salt.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add milk and flour.
Add nuts and fruits. Chill dough for several hours.
Drop by teaspoonful about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Top with 1/2 red or green cherry or pecan half.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: lumberjacks("a sturbridge village cookie")
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add molasses and eggs. Mix well. Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put 1/4 cup sugar into bowl. Pinch off ball of dough about the size of a walnut. Roll into ball. Cover with sugar in bowl.
Place balls on greased cookie sheet 3-inches apart (24 to a cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: delicious baked pot roast
directions: Lay roast on a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil on a cookie sheet.
Spread A-1 sauce over meat.
Spread mushroom soup on top and sprinkle onion soup mix over it.
Wrap tightly in the foil.
Bake about 3 hours at 325°.

title: roast beef gravy
directions: Remove fat from pan, leaving 4 tablespoons.
Set pan on stove. Add flour; brown thoroughly in fat.
Gradually add boiling water. Cook for 5 minutes; season and strain (if needed).

title: chocolate-banana pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Beat sour cream and milk with hand beater until smooth.
Mix in pudding and pie filling (dry) until smooth and slightly thickened.
Slice bananas into pie crust; pour sour cream mixture over bananas.
Refrigerate until set, at least 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings, 360 calories per serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water; add pineapple, cream cheese and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until salad has jelled.
Cut into squares.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour boiling water over corn meal. Add milk, salt, baking powder and butter. Mix and then add beaten eggs. Pour into buttered 1-quart dish. Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, just until set.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add to milk.
Lightly mix in remainder of ingredients.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in shallow pan of water at 350° for 1 hour or until mixture is firm.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Pour liquid off potatoes and mash.
Combine with eggs, milk, sugar, butter and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter until it comes to a boil. Add oats, peanut butter, coconut and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: apple crunch dessert
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch cake pan, pour in the pie filling.
Top with the entire box of cake mix, spreading evenly over pie filling. Melt butter; pour over cake mix.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with chopped pecans the last 5 minutes.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, cornstarch, sugar, cocoa and salt in mixing bowl.
Add egg and sour cream.
Mix until well blended.
Add vanilla, mixing completely.
Fold in chips until well mixed.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Cool and eat.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Heat all ingredients except potatoes to scalding.
Stir in potatoes; continue cooking until smooth, stirring constantly. Soup should be consistency of heavy cream.
Yield: 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: lemon jelly
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, mix together the lemon juice, sugar and pectin.
Bring to a boil, stirring at first to smooth and blend ingredients.
Allow to boil for exactly 2 minutes; remove from heat.

title: scalloped gouda potatoes
directions: Grease deep casserole dish.
Place 1 layer of potato slices in the bottom.
Sprinkle nutmeg, salt, garlic and the peppers.
Cover potatoes next with 1 cup of the cheese.
Cover the cheese with 1/2 of the milk and 1/2 of the cream.
Repeat with a layer of potatoes, spices, cheese, milk and cream.
End with cheese, milk and cream on the very top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: tuna blend sandwich
directions: Open all cans and drain off excess liquid.
Finely chop water chestnuts and olives. Then mix all the ingredients together.
This makes a lot of sandwiches.
The mix can be stored in the fridge for several days.
Great for potlucks.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Mix barbecue sauce, honey and mustard thoroughly and allow the flavors to mix.
Season wingettes to taste and flour.
Heat Canola until very hot for deep frying.
Fry wingettes and allow excess oil to drain.
Stir wingettes into sauce mixture.
Let set 10 minutes.
Serve with Blue cheese dressing and celery sticks. Serves 4.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, flour, eggs and baking powder.
Mix together buttermilk and salt.
Add buttermilk mixture to flavoring and coconut.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° cold oven.
Use a Bundt pan or tube pan, greased and floured.

title: caramel corn
directions: In 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt. Bring to boil, stirring, over medium to high heat, stirring constantly. Boil rapidly to hard-ball stage (260°), about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda quickly, but thoroughly. Pour at once over popcorn in large roasting or baking pan. Stir gently until all kernels are coated. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times during baking. Turn out at once on wax paper. Spread apart and allow to cool. Break apart. Store in tightly covered container.

title: microwave spaghetti
directions: Combine water and saute in microwave.
Save casserole.
Break spaghetti in half and add to sauce.
Make sure the spaghetti is covered with the sauce.
Cover the casserole and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove from the microwave and stir to break up the spaghetti.
Cover again and microwave for another 5 to 7 minutes, stopping several times to stir.
If the mixture is getting too dry, add a little more water.
Yields 1 serving.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk and cocoa together.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, oats and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°. Enjoy!

title: harbin's macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni until firm and drain. Put into pan and add margarine, salt and pepper to taste.
Slice Velveeta cheese into macaroni and half of Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheese.
Add Pet milk until soupy.
Place remaining cheese on top of macaroni and cover pan with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: beef with sour cream
directions: *Ground chuck can be used in place of round steak.
Sprinkle a little Kitchen Bouquet over mixture to add a little color.

title: peppered steak with rice
directions: Cut round steak in 1/4-inch strips. Sprinkle with paprika. Let stand while preparing other ingredients. Brown meat in butter. Add garlic and broth. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onion and peppers.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce. Stir into meat mixture, stirring until clear and thick (2 minutes). Add tomatoes. Stir gently. Serve over bed of rice.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together; beat 1 minute.
Grease and flour pie pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crust.

title: no bake ladyfinger cake
directions: Arrange ladyfingers on bottom and sides of a spring-form pan. Beat whipping cream until stiff; beat in sugar.
Add cream cheese and beat well.
Add pineapple and blend.
Pour half of mixture on ladyfingers.
Add another layer of ladyfingers and pour in the rest of the whipped cream mixture.
Top with blueberry topping. Refrigerate overnight.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Stir flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large bowl; set aside.
Bring cocoa, butter and cola to a boil. Pour over flour mixture.
Beat in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in marshmallows. They float on top of this thin batter.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Cool and frost with icing.

title: homemade meat loaf
directions: Mix ground chuck and sausage meat together thoroughly.
Cut up green bell pepper and white onion in fine pieces.
Mix into meat. Add tomato sauce to meat mixture.
You can also add a little Heinz 57 sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Form meat loaf into a bread loaf.
Cover bottom of pan with foil.
Put meat loaf into pan and cover with more foil.
Cook in oven at 300° for about an hour or until done.
Serves about 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Cut in shortening.
In separate bowl, stir soda into milk and blend this into dry ingredients.
Add yeast to warm water and fold into mixture.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead.
Cut the biscuits and bake in a 375° oven. Remaining dough can be covered and kept in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Makes 48 biscuits.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts just slightly.
Layer a few slices of the ham and then the cheese on half of the chicken.
Fold the other half of the chicken over and secure with toothpicks.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is done and not pink.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped cream. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup cold milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish as desired.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 can rolls in greased 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Combine sugar, cream cheese, egg yolk and vanilla with mixer.
Spread over rolls.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Spread second can of rolls on top of cheese mixture. Spread egg white on top and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes.
Chill and cut.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, add sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add egg yolks and milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Combine 1 stick oleo, boiling water, sugar and salt in a bowl and cool.
Dissolve 1 package dry yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Beat 1 egg (room temperature) and add to yeast mixture.
Add yeast mixture to oleo mixture.
Gradually add 3 cups flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Let rise 1 hour.
With buttered hands, knead dough down; roll on floured surface to 1/4-inch thick.
Pinch pieces and dip in 1 stick melted oleo.
Place in greased Bundt pan and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lentil garlic soup
directions: Saute garlic, onion, carrots and celery in olive oil in large soup pot.
Add lentils, broth, wine and pepper.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: foolproof chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Butter a casserole dish. Arrange breasts on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: lemon lush
directions: First layer, Mix thoroughly, flour, margarine, 2 Tbsp. sugar and nuts.
Press on bottom of 13 x 9 casserole and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Add butter to boiling water, heat until butter melts.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously until ball forms in bottom of pan.
Remove from heat and let cook for 3 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Shape on buttered cookie by dropping from a spoon or using a pastry tube into the shape of a hot dog bun.
Bake until free from beads of moisture (40 to 45 minutes) at 375°.
Cool.
Slice off top of eclair and fill with sweetened whipping cream.
Top with Fudge Sauce.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: peach or apple kuchen
directions: Blend together flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, butter and baking powder and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix in bowl sugar and cinnamon.
Drain off juice, mix together and top bottom layer with 2 pounds peaches or apples or 6 cups sliced.
Bake for 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: ramos fizz
directions: Rub rim of glass with lemon, dip into sugar to frost.
Combine all ingredients, except soda, in a cocktail shaker.
Shake long and steadily until mixture is thick and frothy.
Strain into prepared glass.
Fill with soda.
Serves 1. This can also be done in a blender!
